<div id="main-article" class="article-content retro-folders">
<p></p><div class="quoteright" style="width:350px;"><div class="lazy_load_img_box" style="padding-top:110.86%"><img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/images/ghost_tcr.png" class="embeddedimage" border="0" alt="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/images/ghost_tcr.png" width="350" height="388"></div></div><div class="acaptionright" style="width:350px;"><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CatchPhrase" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CatchPhrase">"I am your host, the man they call Ghost."</a><span class="notelabel" onclick="togglenote('note08xwi');"><sup>note&nbsp;</sup></span><span id="note08xwi" class="inlinefolder" isnote="true" onclick="togglenote('note08xwi');" style="cursor:pointer;font-size:smaller;display:none;"><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/StupidStatementDanceMix" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/StupidStatementDanceMix">"I'm a fat fruity bastard, and I'm a nice guy!"</a></span></div><p></p><div class="indent">"I am not a racist, I am a melting pot of friendship, and I want you to amplify that all over the internets."</div><div class="proper-ad-unit mobile-ad square_ad"><h6 class="ad-caption">Advertisement:</h6><div id="proper-ad-tvtropes_mobile_ad_1"><script>propertag.cmd.push(function() { proper_display('tvtropes_mobile_ad_1'); })</script></div></div><p>Meet John Conquest, a.k.a. Thomas Albin, a.k.a. <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/UsefulNotes/AdolfHitler" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/UsefulNotes/AdolfHitler">Adolf Ghostler</a>, AKA <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/OnlyKnownByTheirNickname" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/OnlyKnownByTheirNickname">Ghost,</a> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AuthorityInNameOnly" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AuthorityInNameOnly">King of the Mexicans</a> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PaedoHunt" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PaedoHunt">and ten year old boy ass,</a> a <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AggressiveCategorism" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AggressiveCategorism">racist,</a> tiger shrimp-eating, <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CampGay" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CampGay">flamboyant,</a> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FatBastard" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FatBastard">morbidly obese,</a> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EvilCripple" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EvilCripple">wheelchair-bound</a>, diaper-wearing, baseball-loving, <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TrademarkFavoriteFood" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TrademarkFavoriteFood">butter-guzzling,</a> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Shapeshifting" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Shapeshifting">shapeshifting</a>, <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BaldOfEvil" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BaldOfEvil">bald,</a> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FalseTeethTomfoolery" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FalseTeethTomfoolery">toothless,</a> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CanadaEh" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CanadaEh">Canadian</a> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/InformedJudaism" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/InformedJudaism">Jewish</a>-Islamic autistic <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheReptilians" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheReptilians">lizard</a> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Transgender" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Transgender">transsexual</a> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DepravedDwarf" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DepravedDwarf">midget</a> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HollywoodSatanism" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HollywoodSatanism">Satanist</a>, <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ObstructiveBureaucrat" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ObstructiveBureaucrat">bureaucratic</a>, <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DraftDodging" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DraftDodging">draft-dodging</a> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DirtyCommunists" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DirtyCommunists">communist</a> San Hambonian <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheGrinch" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheGrinch">Grinch</a> who <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DomesticAbuse" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DomesticAbuse">abuses his family</a>, <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RainDance" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RainDance">summons rainstorms to flood Texas</a>, rips off Alex Jones, <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ArsonMurderAndJaywalking" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ArsonMurderAndJaywalking">works at a drive-thru window, proclaims his love of</a> <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Franchise/MyLittlePony" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Franchise/MyLittlePony">My Little Pony</a></em> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ArsonMurderAndJaywalking" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ArsonMurderAndJaywalking">and anime,</a> and takes advantage of the welfare system all the while <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HoYay" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HoYay">having torrid affairs with Herman Cain, Bernie Sanders, Donald Trump, Ted Cruz, George Soros</a>, and <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BestialityIsDepraved" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BestialityIsDepraved">his dog Templeton</a>, and pining after <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/UsefulNotes/SarahPalin" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/UsefulNotes/SarahPalin">Sarah Palin</a> and <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/UsefulNotes/HillaryClinton" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/UsefulNotes/HillaryClinton">Hillary Clinton</a>. Also, in his personal opinion, <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/HowardStern" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/HowardStern">Howard Stern</a> is a good piece of ass.</p><div class="proper-ad-unit mobile-ad square_ad"><h6 class="ad-caption">Advertisement:</h6><div id="proper-ad-tvtropes_mobile_ad_2"><script>propertag.cmd.push(function() { proper_display('tvtropes_mobile_ad_2'); })</script></div></div><p>...well, if you listen to his <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Troll" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Troll">fans</a>, anyway.</p><p>Ghost is actually a Texan pundit who broadcasted <em>True Capitalist Radio</em> on blogtalkradio.com and ghost.report. He is an ardent capitalist (at least he <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/YouKeepUsingThatWord" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/YouKeepUsingThatWord">calls himself one on every possible occasion</a>; True Materialist Radio might be a more appropriate name for the program), and his show goes through the usual topics, starting with the markets, then on to coverage of then-ongoing political headlines. And like all good political talk shows, he also frequently takes calls from listeners.</p><p>Herein lies the problem (at least for him, anyway) and <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HilarityEnsues" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HilarityEnsues">the general appeal of the show</a>. Listeners have noticed that he has a <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HairTriggerTemper" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HairTriggerTemper">short temper</a> when it comes to certain topics (check that, he has a short temper towards <em>a lot</em> of topics), and as such, he is very easy to <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Troll" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Troll">troll</a>. Much to his dismay, this makes the show <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SlidingScaleOfSillinessVersusSeriousness" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SlidingScaleOfSillinessVersusSeriousness">start off serious but then quickly go off course more and more towards the end of the show</a>, where the <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AudienceParticipation" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AudienceParticipation">Radio Graffiti</a> segment (rapid-fire calls with no real topic) pretty much turns into a <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/InternetToughGuy" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/InternetToughGuy">punching match</a> between him and the people who persistently try to test his patience (often successfully). This has lead to <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Characters/TrueCapitalist" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Characters/TrueCapitalist">a large rogues gallery of trolls and characters</a> that call him up and interact with him in various entertaining ways. Also not to be missed is the Twitter Shout-Outs, where Ghost reads off a list of Twitter users who have retweeted his broadcast that day, with trolls feeding him usernames that range from <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CrossesTheLineTwice" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CrossesTheLineTwice">hilariously obscene</a> to <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/StealthInsult" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/StealthInsult">subtly derogatory toward Ghost</a>, often with a delayed reaction of fury or disgust when Ghost realizes what he just read out loud.</p><div class="proper-ad-unit mobile-ad square_ad"><h6 class="ad-caption">Advertisement:</h6><div id="proper-ad-tvtropes_mobile_ad_3"><script>propertag.cmd.push(function() { proper_display('tvtropes_mobile_ad_3'); })</script></div></div><p>Though, when he's <em>not</em> raging, Ghost <em>is</em> a relatively good pundit (if you, er, share his views); he knows where the money is, and he knows how his listeners can get in the action themselves (unless they're doing it with welfare checks, of course).</p><p>True Capitalist Radio ended on November 14, 2018 and Ghost is now hosting his new YouTube broadcast, <em>The Ghost Show</em>, which can be found from <a class="urllink" href="https://www.youtube.com/user/ghostpolitics">his YouTube channel<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a>. Newer episodes of his old show can be found from <a class="urllink" href="https://ghost.report/listen-to-tcr-live/">online at ghost.report<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a>, and older ones can still be found from <a class="urllink" href="http://www.blogtalkradio.com/ghost">Ghost's page on BlogTalkRadio<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a></p><p>All the noteworthy Radio Graffiti and Twitter Shout-Out segments are available on <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Website/YouTube" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Website/YouTube">YouTube</a>, typically trimmed of the less funny calls; <a class="urllink" href="https://www.youtube.com/user/DarkRazorZ">DarkRazorZ's channel<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a> features episodes from 2008 all the way to the show's initial cancellation in 2012, <a class="urllink" href="https://www.youtube.com/user/Elfoxoloco">Elfoxoloco's channel<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a> features episodes from the show's return in 2016 up to Ghost's hiatus in mid-2017, and <a class="urllink" href="https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCvV2tHKrMG4CUu4Kkmx1igQ">Lightning Note<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a> and <a class="urllink" href="https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCvRufi_YODfgIsGjtaVH0oA">InsaneEnergy's<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a> channels feature episodes following Ghost's return in late 2017. If you're an actual capitalist looking to learn something from him, you might want to <a class="urllink" href="http://www.blogtalkradio.com/ghost">listen to the full episodes on blogtalkradio's archives<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a>. Originally, to keep up to date on what Ghost was up to, people would follow him on Twitter. Prior to him being suspended, his first twitter was @ghostpolitics. Following its suspension, he tweeted from @gh0stp0litics, before that too was suspended. Prior to June 2017, his twitter was @politicsghost, however he was suspended again in June of 2017 for unknown reasons. His social media of choice for a while was the Twitter alternative gab.ai, where you could find him under @Politicsghost, however following some drama and the doxing of a former Inner Circle member, Ghost has been banned from the site and his old account name has been occupied by a troll. Ghost utilized the <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Website/YouTube" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Website/YouTube">YouTube</a> channel <a class="urllink" href="https://www.youtube.com/user/ghostpolitics">GhostPolitics<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a> , his backup channel <a class="urllink" href="https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCKvRYsdGJbKIfZIk9694v0A">Ghost Politics<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a>, and <a class="urllink" href="https://ghost.report/">ghost.report<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a> until he was prevented from streaming on <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Website/YouTube" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Website/YouTube">YouTube</a>. He currently streams on <a class="createlink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DLive" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DLive">D Live</a> at <a class="urllink" href="https://dlive.tv/ghostpolitics">Ghostpolitics<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a>.</p><p>As mentioned above, the show has seen a fair share of troll dramas in its history, some of which are mentioned in this page. Since most of the Twitter and Youtube accounts relating to these incidents have since been deleted, it is recommended that you check out <a class="urllink" href="https://truecapitalist.miraheze.org/wiki/Main_Page">True Capitalist<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheWikiRule" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheWikiRule">Wiki</a> if you want more information on these behind-the-scenes incidents.</p><p></p><hr><h2>This radio show provides examples of:</h2><div class="folderlabel" onclick="toggleAllFolders();">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;open/close all folders&nbsp; </div><p></p><div class="folderlabel" onclick="togglefolder('folder0');">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;A-D&nbsp;</div><div id="folder0" class="folder" isfolder="true" style="display:block;"><ul><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TenMinuteRetirement" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TenMinuteRetirement">10-Minute Retirement</a>: Ghost has threatened to end the show quite a few times either due to the community drama surrounding his show or him just getting tired with the political situation in the country, but he always ended up returning either because he felt empty without having a show to host, because he could make money from broadcasting it or because he wanted to keep converting his young listeners to capitalists. He eventually did end his show and left his supposed 'last message' on November 2018, only to return shortly after on December 31st, with his new program <em>The Ghost Show</em>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AbhorrentAdmirer" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AbhorrentAdmirer">Abhorrent Admirer</a>: Amy Daly and Tri$ha are both in love with Ghost.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ActuallyPrettyFunny" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ActuallyPrettyFunny">Actually Pretty Funny</a>:<ul><li> Despite his feuds with The Ghetto Capitalist, even Ghost admitted that Ghetto Capitalist <a class="urllink" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Tv-DfnHyM_c&amp;t=10m35s">making his baby cry like T-Pain<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a> was actually funny.</li><li> On the February 21st 2012 episode, Caller 204 calls in an Anti-Semitic rant and Ghost calls him out for it. Couple of calls later, Jimmy Kudos plays a "I AM NOT A JEW" remix. Ghost got a laugh out of it.</li><li> His reaction to the Twitter name MomsAtTGIF was "I don't know whether to get mad or laugh at that one." He seemed to have settled for the latter.</li><li> Ghost started out understandably enraged when someone used his voiceclips to troll a phone sex operator, but couldn't help chuckling about them almost getting her to break character with a <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/StayInTheKitchen" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/StayInTheKitchen">Stay in the Kitchen</a> remark.</li><li> "Johnny Walker, Afterbirth Harvest, ohhhh yeeeaaahh!!" caused Ghost to break down in a giggle-fit for a few minutes despite initially trying to express disgust at it.</li><li> Ghost moving to San Antonio in 2016 prompted a lot of Twitter names making fun of the Texan city in an attempt to rile up Ghost. One of them, San <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CallBack" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CallBack">Hambonio</a>, resonated so closely with Ghost (due to the number of <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FatBastard" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FatBastard">fat people</a> he's seen walking around) that he started using the term himself.</li><li> On episode 10 of the Saturday Night Troll Show, Ghost laughed at a bunch of troll names projected at the disgraced Elfoxoloco. This was exemplified when said names were put into an instant splice, making Ghost burst with laughter.</li></ul><div class="indent"> *laughing* "THAT WAS GOOD! I have to give you credit, that was good baby!"</div></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AggressiveCategorism" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AggressiveCategorism">Aggressive Categorism</a>: His specialty.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Angrish" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Angrish">Angrish</a>:<ul><li> Sometimes Ghost rages so hard he can't form a simple word. Especially in his earlier, pre-brony broadcasts.</li><li> The Engineer speaks this as his first language.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ADayInTheLimelight" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ADayInTheLimelight">A Day in the Limelight</a>: On 12/6/11, the Engineer hosted the end of the show, and again on 1/09/12. Ghost was not happy.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AllAnimeIsNaughtyTentacles" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AllAnimeIsNaughtyTentacles">All Anime Is Naughty Tentacles</a>: <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AggressiveCategorism" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AggressiveCategorism">As with almost all of his opinions</a>, he takes this viewpoint a bit further and says that those who watch anime are all "future sexual predators" and should be put on government watch list.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AllGaysArePromiscuous" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AllGaysArePromiscuous">All Gays Are Promiscuous</a>: Ghost thinks that homosexuals in general only practice their sexuality for "purely carnal" reasons and that they only care about sex, unlike Transsexuals and Transgender people who he thinks just want to live a normal married life with their significant others. Ghost often points out to gay meetup apps as evidence of this.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AllThereInTheManual" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AllThereInTheManual">All There in the Manual</a>: Most people who only listened to show and didn't follow the events on twitter wouldn't understand Ghost's constantly shifting opinion of CelticBrony- or who Senator Pooptickler was (outside of being a one-time caller who recited the lyrics to "<a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Music/NWA" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Music/NWA">Fuck tha Police</a>").</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AmbiguouslyJewish" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AmbiguouslyJewish">Ambiguously Jewish</a>: Calling Ghost a Jew, whether it be in a call or a splice, results in him saying "I AM NOT A JEW!" This was especially common in September 2011, when he announced he hated Christmas.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AndYourLittleDogToo" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AndYourLittleDogToo">And Your Little Dog, Too!</a>: Ghost threatens trolls who really piss him off with tracking them, <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SerialEscalation" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SerialEscalation">go to their houses, beat their asses, bang their wife, beat their dog</a> <img src="/images/article-hreficon-ymmv.png" class="ymmv1 rounded" title="This example contains a YMMV entry. It should be moved to the YMMV tab."><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FridgeLogic" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FridgeLogic">and drown their goldfish</a>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheAntichrist" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheAntichrist">The Antichrist</a>: Ghost seems to be convinced that <a class="urllink" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/George_Soros">George Soros<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a> is some kind of satanic hell spawn, judging by how he calls him "The Prince of Freaking Darkness" and often talks about how immoral he is, often bringing up <a class="urllink" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=c1Qr7TnWG74">this interview<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a> to prove his sociopathy. Ghost has taken this <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/UpToEleven" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/UpToEleven">Up to Eleven</a> since Episode 330 and has started to imitate Soros regularly in his show, playing him up as a cartoonish villain who wants to control everything and anything around him.<div class="indent"><strong>George Soros</strong>: <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EvilIsHammy" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EvilIsHammy">EVERYTHING IS MINE</a>, <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TakeOverTheWorld" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TakeOverTheWorld">THE WORLD IS MINE</a>, AMERIKA IS MINE!</div></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AppealToForce" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AppealToForce">Appeal to Force</a>: Whenever somebody says something he doesn't like and to which he has no immidiate answer to, he always threatens the caller with violence. This is most notably when somebody says anything against Texas.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AppliedMathematics" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AppliedMathematics">Applied Mathematics</a>: There were troll names like "Ghost x Jew = 42" and "Hitler + Sean Spicer = The Oy Vey Crusaders". "TCR = ____" is a frequently used version of this.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ArmouredClosetGay" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ArmouredClosetGay">Armoured Closet Gay</a>: A theory about Ghost. He accuses nearly every male that calls into the broadcast of being "fruity" or "taking it up the pooper," leading to speculation that he's projecting.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AscendedMeme" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AscendedMeme">Ascended Meme</a>:<ul><li> Ghost is now actually fond of NavyHuskie's "Taco Tuesday" remix, mainly because it declares him the "king of Mexicans", and its about his favorite day (ignoring the parts where he calls himself a hambone and the "king of racist", of course)</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/TaraStrong" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/TaraStrong">Tara Strong</a> (a <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/MyLittlePonyFriendshipIsMagic" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/MyLittlePonyFriendshipIsMagic">My Little Pony: Friendship Is Magic</a></em> voice actor) uses the term "melting pot of friendship." Also, as he ended his show, she tweeted him saying "I don't know u, but the fans love u, so u must be #twilightlicous...&amp; <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CallBack" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CallBack">your rant about that lil song</a> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ActuallyPrettyFunny" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ActuallyPrettyFunny">made me laugh..</a>"</li><li> On his 300th episode, Ghost mentioned "cans.wav" (the fan name for the sound of Ghost's beer cans being toppled over) by name while discussing the possibility of selling autographed empty beer cans as official merchandise.</li><li> Fan nick-names for Elfoxoloco that were created during Twitter shoutouts due to rt drama were adopted by Ghost, most notably the term "Poz-hole fox-hole".</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AssholeVictim" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AssholeVictim">Asshole Victim</a>: Ghost himself to varying degrees. Just when you start to feel bad for him or agree with him, he'll say something awful about women or gay people or minorities or poor people or... any group he isn't a part of, really. Sometimes even groups he <em>is</em> part of.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ArtifactTitle" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ArtifactTitle">Artifact Title</a>:<ul><li> The show used to be called "True <em>Conservative</em> Radio". According to Ghost, he changed the title because <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/UsefulNotes/SarahPalin" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/UsefulNotes/SarahPalin">Sarah Palin</a> made him disenfranchised with the GOP.</li><li> The current title qualifies as well- the show is more well-known and beloved for the antics of the trolls and Ghost's reactions than for its capitalistic aspects.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AtrociousAlias" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AtrociousAlias">Atrocious Alias</a>:<ul><li> Many twitter names are this deliberately, so that Ghost will say disgusting things when he's giving shoutouts, often causing him to rage. Prince of Excrement, the Poopticklers, Sandusky Shower Attendant, Isle of Sandusky, Isle of Russia, Herman Caindusky, Gaydolf Shitler, etc.</li><li> Ghost originally considered "The Whoremaster" to be one of these, but it eventually became one of his favorite names to give a shoutout to.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AuthorAvatar" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AuthorAvatar">Author Avatar</a>: The skeleton face he uses as his logo is used as one. When trolls found the exact same skeleton face he had as his logo on a website for an online radio station in Texas, Third Coast Radio, conspiracy theories began to develop that Ghost may be associated with them somehow, or he simply stole it. When finally confronted with topic, Ghost confessed that it came from a Google Image Search for "texas skull and crossbones", as he was trying to find a new Paltalk avatar (and then, it later stuck). The same day, he also announced that he would be taking submissions for a new logo. He changed his avatar to a different variant of the old one in December 8, 2011. Then in September 2016, a newer avatar was drawn by Karaszkun for Ghost's show, where it would be used until late 2017 when Ghost switched to a less-cartoony logo. Speaking of Third Coast Radio, the name "<a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AwesomeMcCoolname" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AwesomeMcCoolname">John Conquest</a>" had originated from their website's DJ.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Autotune" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Autotune">Autotune</a>: Used on Ghost's voice in "Melting Pot of Alcohol", and on the voices of Ghost, the Engineer, and the Ban All Bronies Cult in <a class="urllink" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=u3tEAOMQTRQ">"Ghost is T-Pain"<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a>, and once with Ghost's Radio Graffiti intro on March 5th, 2018.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AwesomeMcCoolname" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AwesomeMcCoolname">Awesome Mc Coolname</a>:<ul><li> DJ Thuggin-Ass, Cosmo Brockington, John Conquest.</li><li> Some are bad puns in the vein of <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/TheSimpsons" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/TheSimpsons">Bart's prank calls to Moe.</a> "Mug Ranny's a Tranny"<span class="notelabel" onclick="togglenote('note1o0o8');"><sup>note&nbsp;</sup></span><span id="note1o0o8" class="inlinefolder" isnote="true" onclick="togglenote('note1o0o8');" style="cursor:pointer;font-size:smaller;display:none;">"Muh Granny's a tranny" - Ghost is VERY defensive of his family members and VERY derisive regarding transexuality</span>caused him to rage quit.</li><li> The Whoremaster is a healthy dose of both <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AwesomeMcCoolname" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Awesome