ng</a>: The end of the show's original run. Bitter in that the show had a lot of life left in it and a tiger shrimp/Karaszkun story arc of sorts looked like it was about to get off the ground before being abruptly cut off; sweet in that most everybody involved got a <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HappilyEverAfter" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HappilyEverAfter">pretty happy ending.</a><ul><li> Ghost's final show on Blog Talk Radio on March 27th, 2018 before moving to ghost.report may count as this, since he's no longer getting paid due to BTR being bought by Spreaker. It's a shame to see Ghost leaving BTR for good, but the show will move on to somewhere out there...</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BlackComedy" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BlackComedy">Black Comedy</a>: Some of the Twitter names can also fall into this trope, often poking fun at (then-current) tragedies, natural disasters, and crimes.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BlackComedyRape" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BlackComedyRape">Black Comedy Rape</a>: "<a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ManipulativeEditing" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ManipulativeEditing">The next subject I'd like to talk about is...</a> <img src="/images/article-hreficon-ymmv.png" class="ymmv1 rounded" title="This example contains a YMMV entry. It should be moved to the YMMV tab."><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CrossesTheLineTwice" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CrossesTheLineTwice">rape</a>."</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BookBurning" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BookBurning">Book Burning</a>: Or autograph burning in this case. Numerous people bought Ghost's autograph just to burn it and tweet Ghost an image of them doing it. Ghost was not pleased.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Bookends" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Bookends">Bookends</a>: Th