fter the original calls.</li></ul><div class="indent"><strong>Caller:</strong> Johnnie Walker, <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Squick" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Squick">567th harvest</a>, oh yeah...</div></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BrokenPedestal" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BrokenPedestal">Broken Pedestal</a>: Several for Ghost<ul><li> He used to admire United States for what it was, but has since come to utterly despise it's population as ignorant ghettofied socialists who are too distracted by <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/AmericanIdol" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/AmericanIdol">American Idol</a> and <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/DancingWithTheStars" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/DancingWithTheStars">Dancing with the Stars</a> to actually care about what's happening to the country<div class="indent">"WHAT HAPPENED TO AMERICA!? WHAT HAPPENED TO THE GODDAMN AMERICA!? WE USED TO BE THE BASTION, THE BASTION OF CAPITALISM! BUT NOW WE ARE THE BASTARDS, THE BASTARDS OF CAPITALISM!"</div></li><li> He used to be a devout follower and supporter of the Republican Party, however both the corruption within the party and and what he views as the "liberalization" of the party by <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/UsefulNotes/SarahPalin" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/UsefulNotes/SarahPalin">Sarah Palin</a> and John McCain ultimately caused Ghost to abandon the Conservative movement as a whole. <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HowWeGotHere" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HowWeGotHere">He has since started to refer to himself as a Capitalist</a>.</li><li> He used to view <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/ValveSoftware" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/ValveSoftware">Gabe Newell</a> as a fellow capitalist. However, all admiration for him ended when he got to hear live on the broadcast <a class="urllink" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=-vvS7Q1pSd4">that Gabe is a brony.<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a></li><li> He was also a strong supporter of <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/UsefulNotes/GeorgeWBush" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/UsefulNotes/GeorgeWBush">George W. Bush</a> even after leaving the Conservative movement. However starting with 2016 Ghost has been extremely critical of Bushes, referring to them as "The Bush Crime Family" book called "Jeb! and the Bush Crime Family: The Inside Story of an American Dynasty" written by Ghost's "associate" Roger Stone.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ButtMonkey" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ButtMonkey">Butt-Monkey</a>: Ghost is the butt monkey of his own show!</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CampGay" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CampGay">Camp Gay</a>: <a class="urllink" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=lZjcSA9luic">Caller 111<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a>/The Internet Buttstalker, who calls in a ridiculously effeminate voice while making <em>very</em> suggestive requests.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CanadaEh" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CanadaEh">Canadia, Eh?</a>: Ghost seems to have a thing against Canada for some reason...<div class="indent">"Y'know, there's something very <em>Canadian</em> about you calling me from the tub."</div><ul><li> According to Ghost he hates Canada because they booed the national anthem a few days after 9/11.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Catchphrase" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Catchphrase">Catchphrase</a>: Because of the amount of catch phrases Ghost has, <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Catchphrase/TrueCapitalist" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Catchphrase/TrueCapitalist">he had to be given his own page.</a></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheChessmaster" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheChessmaster">The Chessmaster</a>: CelticBrony claimed to be this after his doxxing, but few actually believed him until months later, when Ghost's twitter account was hacked and it turned out that he <em>wasn't</em> lying about having a master plan. Apparently MrTacoz and Ibanezzo were in on it the whole time, and the NCF were involved somehow.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ChewToy" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ChewToy">Chew Toy</a>: Ghost just keeps doggedly ploughing calls as troll after troll drive him to rage and <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Angrish" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Angrish">angrish</a>, and that's why he's popular.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ChristmasEpisode" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ChristmasEpisode">Christmas Episode</a>:<ul><li> September 19, 2011 certainly felt like one. Just yesterday he had revealed that he thought it was too early for <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ChristmasSongs" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ChristmasSongs">Christmas Songs</a>. Of course, it backfired, in the usual ways.</li><li> December 24, 2011: Ghost did a legitimate Christmas Eve special.</li><li> December 24, 2016: Ghost did another Christmas Eve special, 5 years after the last one.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CircleOfShame" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CircleOfShame">Circle of Shame</a>: The chatroom serves as this in Ghost's worst moments:<div class="indent"> "Look at 'em, they're laughing for Christ's sake!"</div></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ClipShow" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ClipShow">Clip Show</a>: December 31, 2011 brought the "Ghosties", a listener-voted awards show that honored the trolls. Among other things, "Melting Pot of Alcohol" got Best Remix, "Money, Success, Fame, Bronies" for best splice, Surgeradio.org guy for best fail troll, CelticBrony for best brony, and Ghetto Capitalist for best troll.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ClusterFBomb" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ClusterFBomb">Cluster F-Bomb</a>: Ghost lost his mind on June 7th, 2016 after too many diaper jokes and no longer "excused his French".<ul><li> He also used the F-word very liberally (<a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NoPunIntended" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NoPunIntended">No Pun Intended</a>) in his infamous April 24th 2016 two hour Anime rant.</li><li> He also used the F-Word multiple times near the end of Episode 433 <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DudeNotFunny" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DudeNotFunny">when a caller made a joke about child pornography</a> and gave away the caller's phone number.</li><li> After leaving BTR, his F-Word quotient rose exponentially.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ComicallyMissingThePoint" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ComicallyMissingThePoint">Comically Missing the Point</a>:<ul><li> If you're going to use the "<a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SomeOfMyBestFriendsAreX" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SomeOfMyBestFriendsAreX">I have black friends</a>" clich&eacute; to prove you're not a racist, don't go on to claim you also have friends who are "wop", "camel jockey" and "kraut".</li><li> On February 28th 2012, a listener called in and told Ghost that he sprained his wrist while <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ADateWithRosiePalms" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ADateWithRosiePalms">masturbating in the bathroom stall at work</a>, giving him a month's worth of worker's compensation. Ghost was only shocked by the fact that the caller was autotuning himself.</li></ul><div class="indent"> "Aww, T-Pain hung up!"</div><ul><li> His January 25th 