rse" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/InUniverse">In-Universe</a> example: Ghost smoked "Tetrahydrocannabinol", as he called it, on 4/20 to show kids that they shouldn't. He then proceeded to be extremely calm, giving long-winded rants on existential subjects and reacting to trolls with simple apathy.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DownerEnding" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DownerEnding">Downer Ending</a>:<ul><li> The end of the show on May 6th, 2017. Unlike last time where the community made up and left on a high note with a final goodbye from Ghost, this one feels as though the community has gradually grown more distant from Ghost, due in part to the Inner Circle but also due to how him and others have been conducting themselves. And despite his claims of a return, there is now no longer a solid date, leaving TCR's future unknown. Fortunately, <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheBusCameBack" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheBusCameBack">Ghost returned on October 31st, 2017</a>.</li><li> Happened once again in November 14th, 2018. The show had been going downhill in terms of viewers since the end of shoutouts and radio graffiti and Ghost was becoming frustrated that nobody was listening to his show. This was made even worse by the results of the 2018 midterms, as Ghost was very angry over the new demographic of the people elected to the House, as well as the demographics of the people who elected them. Ghost made several rant filled episodes about how he wished than an open borders policy would be enacted so that the immigrants could beat the hell out of this new demographic and how video games should be regulated like pornography and entirely banned from people under the age of 21 or those diagnosed with autism/Asperger/mental disorders. This was seen by most of his remaining listeners as a betrayal of the core values that he stood for and even his most loyal fans now ended up leaving the community. The show ended with Ghost being left as a bitter wreck who believed Western civilization's destruction to be imminent and with only a handful of people still listening to his show.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DudeNotFunny" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DudeNotFunny">Dude, Not Funny!</a>: People usually bombard Twitter (and when he had it, the chatroom) with names with the sole purpose of setting Ghost off.<ul><li> As seen in the comments section of <a class="urllink" href="https://youtu.be/Uig2bbHgJ5c">this video<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a>, Some in the fandom believe that bombarding Ghost with Vietnam references with the intention of setting him off is over the line. His reactions seem to be genuinely on the verge of mentally and emotionally breaking down, and at least once he has had to step away from the mic due to it, which is something he rarely does unless something <em>really</em> gets to him. Considering that he very possibly <em>is</em> a veteran of Vietnam with unpleasant memories of it...</li><li> Pizzagate/pedophilia jokes will illicit this reaction. Ghost ended a show 20 minutes early due to a caller making one of these, and threatened to end a Troll Show 40 minutes early due to a splice of this.</li><li> He'll freak out if <em>anyone</em> tries to make humor around an unfortunate event, <em>especially</em> if it involves the death of a major figure, or it happened in Texas (i.e. the constant Texas Fire jokes)</li><li> On the day of the SOPA/PIPA protest, one caller made a splice to make it sound like Ghost supports it (even though he's been vocally anti-SOPA). Even the people in the chatroom called it too soon.</li><li> He even reacted like this to a username that made fun of the Titanic. Yes, the same Titanic the sunk in 1912</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DumbIsGood" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DumbIsGood">Dumb Is Good</a>: In the October 18's broadcast, Ghost expresses a love for the mentally retarded.<ul><li> Ghost's <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ScienceIsBad" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ScienceIsBad">hostility towards NASA, Stephen Hawking and science in general</a> might stem from this.</li></ul></li></ul></div><div class="folderlabel" onclick="togglefolder('folder1');">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;E-H&nbsp;</div><div id="folder1" class="folder" isfolder="true" style="display:block;"><ul><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EarlyBirdCameo" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EarlyBirdCameo">Early-Bird Cameo</a>:<ul><li> KaraszKun was given a twitter shoutout right before the Ghosties awards on December 31st, 2011. He also had another one later on when he called Ghost and told him, out of genuine concern, to calm down before he has a heart attack. Ironiclly, Ghost actually raged at him over this.</li><li> Kermit The Frog of <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Franchise/TheMuppets" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Franchise/TheMuppets">The Muppets</a> fame called up exactly once in 2012 to troll Ghost's hatred of bronies. During the post-revival era, however, Kermit has become a regular member of the rogues gallery, and has pissed off Ghost on numerous occasions in 2016.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EarlyInstallmentWeirdness" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EarlyInstallmentWeirdness">Early Installment Weirdness</a>: Up until 2010, his show was really a fairly ordinary, if rather extreme, far-right radio show.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EnemyEatsYourLunch" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EnemyEatsYourLunch">Enemy Eats Your Lunch</a>: In Episode 329, Ghost claims that a DHS agent not only ate one of his chips, but double dipped it into his salsa.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EnemyMine" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EnemyMine">Enemy Mine</a>: While he's been an avid critic of Alex Jones for a long time, he became significantly more supporting of him after hearing that he was supporting Donald Trump for president, going as far as to call him a good capitalist. When describing his opinion of Alex Jones, Ghost specifically referred to this trope by name, stating that the 2016 election was so important he was willing to cut Jones some slack.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EnsembleCast" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EnsembleCast">Ensemble Cast</a>: Oh yes. Even discounting the main crew of trolls and capitalists, there are a massive number of splicers who usually show up on twitter or call in only occasionally (The Harbingerr, Navy Huskie, Alex S, Elfoxoloco, DarkRazorZ, Coodoo17 etc.)</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EvenEvilHasStandards" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EvenEvilHasStandards">Even Evil Has Standards</a>: Ghost says a lot of nasty things about a lot of people, but certain things like mocking people's deaths, making fun of natural disasters, making threats on the President's life (Even <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/UsefulNotes/BarackObama" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/UsefulNotes/BarackObama">Barack Obama</a>), child abuse/molestation, and <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ArsonMurderAndJaywalking" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ArsonMurderAndJaywalking">the twitter name "Bullets4Bronies"</a> are considered uncalled for or going too far by him. As much as he dislikes Canada, he thinks names wishing death on the country and making fun of the Spring 2016 Fort <a class="createlink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/McMurray" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/McMurray">Mc Murray</a> wildfires were also going too far.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EveryoneHasStandards" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EveryoneHasStandards">Everyone Has Standards</a>: Ghost is a jerkass but as noted above, he has standards, sometimes comes to the protection of the Engineer or other members of the "cast" if they're being pushed too hard, and calls out trolls who <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DudeNotFunny" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DudeNotFunny">take a joke too far</a>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EveryoneCallsHimBarkeep" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EveryoneCallsHimBarkeep">Everyone Calls Him "Barkeep"</a>: The Engineer.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EverythingIsBigInTexas" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EverythingIsBigInTexas">Everything Is Big in Texas</a>: Said verbatim in the 8/18/11 show.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ExactWords" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ExactWords">Exact Words</a>: He said that <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/YourMom" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/YourMom">your mother</a> was at T.G.I. Friday's looking for "Alabama black snake." Presumably ABS is an obscure cocktail that few of us have heard of, and <em>not</em> a black man's penis?</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FatBastard" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FatBastard">Fat Bastard</a>: Ghost actually called one of his younger trolls this. <img src="/images/article-hreficon-ymmv.png" class="ymmv1 rounded" title="This example contains a YMMV entry. It should be moved to the YMMV tab."><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CrossesTheLineTwice" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CrossesTheLineTwice">The troll reacted by pretending to have an orgasm.</a></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FaceHeelTurn" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FaceHeelTurn">Face&#150;Heel Turn</a>: Equestrian Citizen <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheReveal" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheReveal">revealed himself</a> to be <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PrettyFlyForAWhiteGuy" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PrettyFlyForAWhiteGuy">a white guy using a voice changer</a> and promptly began sucking up to Ghost.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FilkSong" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FilkSong">Filk Song</a>: <a class="urllink" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=eYS4h8ku-5E">A trans-testicle woman sings a homoerotic love song to Ghost<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a>, to the tune and semi-lyrics of <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Music/OneDirection" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Music/OneDirection">"What Makes You Beautiful"</a>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FiveManBand" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FiveManBand">Five-Man Band</a>:<ul><li> Early lineup:<ul><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheHero" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheHero">The Hero</a> &#151; Internet Buttstalker</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheLancer" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheLancer">The Lancer</a> &#151; Spermy the Cat</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheSmartGuy" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheSmartGuy">The Smart Guy</a> &#151; Tzeki</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheBigGuy" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheBigGuy">The Big Guy</a> - IbanEzzo</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheChick" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheChick">The Chick</a> &#151; The Aborted Fetus</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheSixthRanger" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheSixthRanger">The Sixth Ranger</a> &#151; CelticBrony</li></ul></li><li> 2012 lineup:<ul><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheHero" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheHero">The Hero</a> &#151; Ghetto Capitalist</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheLancer" ti