kie</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheSmartGuy" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheSmartGuy">The Smart Guy</a> &#151; CosmoBrockington</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheBigGuy" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheBigGuy">The Big Guy</a> &#151; FatMarshall</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheChick" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheChick">The Chick</a> &#151; Fapitalist</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheSixthRanger" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheSixthRanger">The Sixth Ranger</a> &#151; Coodoo17</li></ul></li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FlatWorld" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FlatWorld">Flat World</a>: While Ghost doesn't support flat earth theory, he strongly believes that Earth isn't spheroid in shape and that space doesn't exist. Ghost has also supported several theories made by flat earthers such as the theory that Antarctica forms an impenetrable wall along the circumference of the Earth-disk which the government tries to hide (despite plenty of evidence to the contrary) and that the apparent curvature of the horizon is actually caused by the curvature of lenses, which lead to him attacking <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/UsefulNotes/NeilDeGrasseTyson" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/UsefulNotes/NeilDeGrasseTyson">Neil deGrasse Tyson</a> on twitter for saying that earth is "pear shaped". <span class="notelabel" onclick="togglenote('note2140x');"><sup>note&nbsp;</sup></span><span id="note2140x" class="inlinefolder" isnote="true" onclick="togglenote('note2140x');" style="cursor:pointer;font-size:smaller;display:none;">What DeGrasse actually meant by this is how in relative sense Earth is pear shaped since it's slightly wider just south of the Equator based on data collected with satellites, obviously not something you can just see with the naked eye.</span></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Foreshadowing" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Foreshadowing">Foreshadowing</a>: Occasionally, a shout-out name that Ghost mentions in the episode would be spliced later for Radio Graffiti. And in some cases, the very same episode. Ghost <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LampshadeHanging" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LampshadeHanging">lamp-shaded</a> on this matter in Troll Show Episode 9:<div class="indent"> "<em>Ghost Want a Cracker</em>? ...You know I gotta I gotta be careful about reading some of these names 'cause some of you people are trying to get me to say something so you could splice the son of a bitch."</div></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ForcedMeme" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ForcedMeme">Forced Meme</a>: Ghost tried to advocate the use of the term "hambone" to insult who he considers to be overweight people who contribute nothing to society. The trolls gladly helped it become a popular meme... by splicing clips of Ghost calling <em>himself</em> a hambone.<div class="indent"> Ghost, from True Capitalist Radio, is a HAM-BOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOONE.</div></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GameMod" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GameMod">Game Mod</a>:<ul><li> <em><a class="urllink" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=JESMEBaSpyM">True Capitalist<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/DOOM" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/DOOM">DOOM</a>: Bronies on Earth</em>. Replacing various weapons and powerups with various happenings on the show, such as a "Can crusher" shotgun, a pearl launcher as the rocket launcher, a hadoken for the <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BFG" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BFG">BFG</a>, and invulnerability being "Chatroom Martial Law". Although the enemy sprites weren't changed, they did receive some voices and names such as the Fruitbowl (Imp) or FU Texas Beast (CyberDemon, which of course, plays "Fuck You Texas" when it's alerted). Currently, the mod's availible as a .pk3 that can be mounted over other DOOM .wads in a sourceport such as ZDoom or Skulltag. Ghost himself claimed he actually liked the DOOM mod. Probably due to the fact he gets to be a major badass among the same level as the DOOM Guy.</li><li> Other independent fan games are also being produced, such as MetroidJunkie's first-person shooter "<a class="urllink" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=5oL1RAWwwzk">Capitalist Chaos: Freedom vs. Fruitbowl<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a>" and J-Man's "<a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/PacMan" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/PacMan">Mrs. Ghostman</a>", a retro-style game starring Ghost's wife.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GiantSpaceFleaFromNowhere" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GiantSpaceFleaFromNowhere">Giant Space Flea from Nowhere</a>: The NCF (or someone claiming to be a member, at least) suddenly hacking Ghost and making him quit True Capitalist Radio on May 23rd, 2012.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GodzillaThreshold" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GodzillaThreshold">Godzilla Threshold</a>: After <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DespairEventHorizon" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DespairEventHorizon">Newt Gingrich won the South Carolina primary,</a> Ghost was so disgusted with the crop of Republican candidates that he considered supporting Ron Paul. He has also considered moving to "Canadia" since, in his words, they're getting more capitalist than America</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GodwinsLaw" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GodwinsLaw">Godwin's Law</a>: Ghost is relatively tame about using this compared to <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Radio/GlennBeck" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Radio/GlennBeck">some other</a> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Radio/RushLimbaugh" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Radio/RushLimbaugh">right-wing</a> radio hosts, but he still invokes it from time to time.<ul><li> He claims that the Nazis experimented with water fluoridation on death camps as part of his water fluoridation conspiracy <span class="notelabel" onclick="togglenote('note3iypa');"><sup>note&nbsp;</sup></span><span id="note3iypa" class="inlinefolder" isnote="true" onclick="togglenote('note3iypa');" style="cursor:pointer;font-size:smaller;display:none;"> <a class="urllink" href="http://www.politifact.com/florida/statements/2011/oct/06/critics-water-fluoridation/truth-about-fluoride-doesnt-include-nazi-myth/">they didn't<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a> </span>.</li><li> He most commonly uses this trope when he talks about George Soros. He <em>loves</em> reminding his audience about how Soros collaborated with the Nazis against his own Jewish people whenever talking about the man. <span class="notelabel" onclick="togglenote('note4jwmi');"><sup>note&nbsp;</sup></span><span id="note4jwmi" class="inlinefolder" isnote="true" onclick="togglenote('note4jwmi');" style="cursor:pointer;font-size:smaller;display:none;"> He witnessed confiscations of Jewish property when disguised as the son of a Hungarian government official, but never actually took part in them himself. </span><div class="indent"><strong>Ghost talking with heavy Hungarian accent</strong>: ...And what I did to stop the Nazis from putting me into concentration camp is I gave my ass to Goebbels and to Himmler and to Joseph Mengele and and and they left me alone and they didn't touch me, so I decided that I was going to sell out my own Jew and it was the happiest time of my life. That's where I became <em>The Prince of Darkness</em>.</div><