</a></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HopeSpot" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HopeSpot">Hope Spot</a>: Ghost has one in his Sept. 23, 2016, broadcast, where he's competing against the Engineer to see who can sell more autographs. He brings himself into a near-emotional breakdown at the prospect of the Engineer winning over him, until he sees how far of a lead he has over his employee. This gives him a sense of relief... until he sees what people on Twitter have been <em>doing</em> with his autographs: defacing them in disgusting ways, burning them, and photoshopping them with his enemies and other unpopular figures endorsing them.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HostileShowTakeover" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HostileShowTakeover">Hostile Show Takeover</a>: <a class="urllink" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=G7eS7NTMeWk&amp;feature=g-u">The Engineer, of all people<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HufflepuffHouse" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HufflepuffHouse">Hufflepuff House</a>: Several fandoms have lurked TCR in its history but failed to gain the same attention as bronies and anime fans.<ul><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/TouhouProject" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/TouhouProject">Touhou</a> fans have trolled Ghost as far back as summer 2011, but they never gained as much prominence in the show as Bronies and general Anime fandoms, but haven't exactly fallen to obscurity on the show either and have gained more attention from Ghost and the community than the other fandoms listed here.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/SpongebobSquarepants" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/SpongebobSquarepants">Spongies</a> and <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/ThomasTheTankEngine" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/ThomasTheTankEngine">Tankies</a> similarly to Touhou fans have trolled Ghost for since late 2011-early 2012, but never gained much of a spotlight and where just considered annoying by most listeners and Ghost himself.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Webcomic/Homestuck" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Webcomic/Homestuck">[1]</a> fans tried to troll the show in late in late 2012 but the lack of reaction from Ghost and the hatred they gained from rest of the community quickly drove them away.</li><li> Initially, it looked like <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/Undertale" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/Undertale">Undertale</a> fandom might become the next big thing after the bronies since the show returned around the time that the game's hype was at it's peak. Ultimately Undertale related trolling didn't resonate well with Ghost or the trolls among whom the game had a large <img src="/images/article-hreficon-flamebait.png" class="flamebait1 rounded" title="This example contains a FlameBait entry. It should be moved to the FlameBait tab."><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Hatedom" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Hatedom">Hatedom</a>. Undertale saw a short return to fame after Ghost was informed that the game was "Anime related" and Teutonic Plague was accused of playing it and G came out of the closet as an Undertale fan (but was surprisingly enough able to eventually convince Ghost that Undertale wasn't related to Hentai or Anime).</li><li> The <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/FiveNightsAtFreddys" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/FiveNightsAtFreddys">FNAF</a> fandom has made appearances in the show from time to time, mostly bombarding Ghost with pizza related Twitter names.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/StevenUniverse" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/StevenUniverse">Steven Universe</a> calls have occasionally appeared in 2017, with little to no reaction from Ghost.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HumiliationConga" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HumiliationConga">Humiliation Conga</a>:<ul><li> Have the calls started? If so, then this trope is now in effect.</li><li> Inflicted on CelticBrony by the Capitalist Army and the Ghetto Capitalist Army.</li><li> The Inner Circle Short Bus copied this from Inner Circle members and Ghost himself.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Hypocrite" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Hypocrite">Hypocrite</a>: Where do we even start?<ul><li> Ghost rages at those who accuse Obama's critics of being racist, but he willingly accuse anyone who mocks or criticises Herman "Sugar" Cain of being racist, taken <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/UpToEleven" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/UpToEleven">Up to Eleven</a> when he tried to use this argument against Ghetto Capitalist.</li><li> <a class="urllink" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=-FbyCYrP0FU">In "Ghost's Valentine,"<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a> he tells Shut Up Mom Guy to "stop talking to your mother that way, you son of a bitch!"</li><li> He accuses liberals of using <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LogicalFallacies" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LogicalFallacies">Logical Fallacies</a> to win arguments, even though he himself frequently resorts to <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AdHominem" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AdHominem">name-calling</a> and <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/StrawmanFallacy" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/StrawmanFallacy">strawmanning</a> when debating with people he disagrees with. This is especially noticeable whenever he's talking about Stephen Hawking, who Ghost claims isn't a valid scientific authority because he's physically deformed.</li><li> During the <a class="urllink" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=jMogFcNeK04">July 17th broadcast<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a>, Ghost states that he doesn't like <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Website/YouTube" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Website/YouTube">YouTube</a> personalities because they're "self-important" and "idiots" in his opinion.</li><li> Once after receiving a series of misogynist calls, Ghost points out that the hateful speech against women practiced by the trolls will ultimately lead to tighter internet regulation that they seem to oppose. Of course while saying this, Ghost forgot to bring up the various times he acts hatefully towards women in his show, ranging from him telling them to <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/StayInTheKitchen" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/StayInTheKitchen">Stay in the Kitchen</a> to calling them "Skankasauruses" and outright advocating violence against them.</li><li> Ghost has been strongly critical of communist leaders such as <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/UsefulNotes/JosefStalin" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/UsefulNotes/JosefStalin">Josef Stalin</a> and <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/UsefulNotes/MaoZedong" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/UsefulNotes/MaoZedong">Mao Zedong</a> for the millions of deaths their regimes caused, but when discussing <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/UsefulNotes/AugustoPinochet" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/UsefulNotes/AugustoPinochet">Augusto Pinochet</a>, Ghost focused on how his capitalist reforms made Chile into one of South America's most successful economies, and when discussing the massacres he says that the thousands of victims of extrajudicial killings were all leftist hippies and guerrillas who deserved to die anyway and that he was <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/JustDoingMyJob" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/JustDoingMyJob">"just protecting his country."</a> Granted, Pinochet didn't have nearly as high a body count as the aforementioned dictators, but that still undermines Ghost's claim that he's opposed to authoritarianism.</li><li> Ghost has a great hatred for millennials because he views them among many other things as self centered and egotistical, even though he himself constantly engages in self-fawning throughout his broadcasts and took it to truly ridiculous levels when he gave himself an award in <a class="urllink" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Nyyp3Fu8zrI">the 500th episode award show<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a></li><li> Ghost hates <em>anything</em> fiction based, be it books, video games or movies, because he feels that fiction is disconnecting people from reality, yet just taking a quick look at <a class="urllink" href="https://truecapitalist.miraheze.org/wiki/Conspiracy_Theories">Conspiracy Theories page on the TCR wiki<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a> showcases how badly Ghost himself is out of touch with reality.</li><li> Ghost criticizes people who watch cartoons as manchildren, yet he throws temper tantrums like a child, despite being a man in his 60's.</li><li> Ghost often tells trolls to kill themselves and grow up, and frequently adds to this insults directed at their loved ones and living situations. However, trolls who do this to him or people he supports are usually the recipients of his rage and retaliation in the form of being removed from the broadcast, being booted from the chat room or, rarely, prematurely ending the show.</li><li> Ghost tends to insult the younger generation of Americans on the grounds of laziness, entitlement attitudes, apathy, refusal to own their choices, and overall stupidity. However, on nearly every show he rants about deserving respect and, among other things, playing the victim by holding the trolls responsible for his drinking behavior and temper-tantrums. For an individual who is extremely critical of the younger generations of Americans not taking responsibility for the problems they supposedly create, he does not do a good job of being accountable for his own choices via playing the victim and demanding respect, even when his actions do not reflect the same towards others.</li><li> Ghost will rage to the point of losing his voice if anyone so much as suggests that Texas sucks. Of course, he has no problem ripping on other states...especially California and Oklahoma.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HypocriticalHumour" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HypocriticalHumour">Hypocritical Humour</a>: Beginning in November 2016, Ghost wanted people to start taking pedophilia and Pizzagate seriously and threatened to have anyone who made fun of pedophilia doxed... only for Ghost himself to crack a pedophile joke about Milo Yiannopoulos. This was later <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LampshadeHanging" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LampshadeHanging">lampshaded</a> by a troll in <a class="urllink" href="https://youtu.be/XNv6q1cHWGA?t=1m38s">a splice that aired a few days after Ghost made the joke<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a>.</li></ul></div><div class="folderlabel" onclick="togglefolder('folder2');">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;I-Q&nbsp;</div><div id="folder2" class="folder" isfolder="true" style="display:block;"><ul><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/IAmTheTrope" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/IAmTheTrope">I Am the Trope</a>:<ul><li> On the 12/06/11 show, Ghost said "I <em>am</em> Blog Talk Radio!"</li><li> He also frequently said "I <em>am</em> the underground!"</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/IdiosyncraticEpisodeNaming" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/IdiosyncraticEpisodeNaming">Idiosyncratic Episode Naming</a>: After True Capitalist Radio stopped being just another show to troll and became basically an online sitcom with characters and an (unwilling) <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/UnsympatheticComedyProtagonist" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/UnsympatheticComedyProtagonist">Unsympathetic Comedy Protagonist</a>, DarkRazorZ began naming the episodes when he uploaded them onto Youtube. They're usually named after the best troll of the day or a running gag throughout the episode ("12 Year Old Vs Ghost," "Engineer's Escapades", "RIP Steve Jobs," "Spectator's Spectacular Testicles," etc.)</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/IKnewIt" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/IKnewIt">I Knew It!</a>: <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/InUniverse" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/InUniverse">In-Universe</a>.<ul><li> <a class="urllink" href="https://twitter.com/#!/ghostpolitics/status/160089343208325121">He guessed right that the Megaupload controversy was a trap<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a>.</li><li> He knew the whole <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DomesticAbuse" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DomesticAbuse">Domestic Abuse</a> situation with Asho in November was all a setup.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ILied" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ILied">I Lied</a>: Ghost claimed that his final show would be on March 9th, 2012. As it turned out, there was no show on that date, and it was merely an attempt to troll the trolls.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/IncomingHam" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/IncomingHam">Incoming Ham</a>:<div class="indent"> Well folks, I think it's time for everybody's favorite part of the broadcast, AND I'M TALKIN' ABOUT <em>RADIO GRAFFITIIIIII</em>! Hahahahaaaa!</div><ul><li> "Ghost baby what's goin' on?!"</li><li> "SUCK MAH DIIIIIIIIIIIIIIIIIIIIIIIIIIIIIIICK, SUCK MAH DIIIIIIIIIIIIIIIIIICK-"</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/INeedAFreakingDrink" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/INeedAFreakingDrink">I Need a Freaking Drink</a>: "Cause drinking is what I like to do~!"</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/InternetToughGuy" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/InternetToughGuy">Internet Tough Guy</a>: "YOU'RE LUCKY WE'RE NOT IN A GODDAMN BARROOM BECAUSE I'D BEAT THE LIVING BAJEZUS OUT'A YOU!"</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/InsaneTrollLogic" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/InsaneTrollLogic">Insane Troll Logic</a>:<ul><li> 9/27/11: A guy says an old <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Meme" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Meme">meme</a>. According to Ghost, it's why America is going down the toilet. No, it does not make sense in context.</li><li> He makes fun of ethnic minorities like there is no tomorrow. He's not a racist, though!.<ul><li> Ditto for the members of LGBT community (though he has a soft spot for transgender people).</li></ul></li><li> Despite going on multiple rants about how he doesn't drink coffee, he has also denied being Jewish by saying "I use yarmulkes for coffee filters"</li><li> During one episode, Ghost told all the listeners who opposed his bizarre and crazy conspiratorial beliefs that them calling him a tinfoil hat wearer is contributing to government censorship and will bring an end to free speech.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/InsultBackfire" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/InsultBackfire">Insult Backfire</a>: Any insult Ghost tries to use on the trolls will either be ignored, accepted with glee, used against him, or turned into <em>yet another</em> remix. "Hambone", which he invented to subtly insult overweight people. The trolls turned it against him almost immediately.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/IntercontinuityCrossover" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/IntercontinuityCrossover">Intercontinuity Crossover</a>: "I GOT MY LITTLE PONY CHARACTERS CALLING ME NOW"</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/InterruptingMeme" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/InterruptingMeme">Interrupting Meme</a>: "SUCK MAH DIIIIICK!"</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/IReadItForTheArticles" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/IReadItForTheArticles">I Read It for the Articles</a>: Some people actually listen to Ghost for his political opinions.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Irony" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Irony">Irony</a>: During the July 9th, 2016 broadcast, a splice is made of Ghost creating <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FrankensteinsMonster" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FrankensteinsMonster">Frankenstein's Monster</a> while <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LaughingMad" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LaughingMad">laughing insanely</a>. While the splice itself made Ghost angry, what truly set him off is that the splice makes him sound psychotic, which <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BlatantLies" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BlatantLies">he clearly isn't</a>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ItsAllAboutMe" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ItsAllAboutMe">It's All About Me</a>: "I'M THE TALENT! ME! NOT THE ENGINEER! ME!"</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/IsThisThingOn" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/IsThisThingOn">Is This Thing On?</a>: How Ghost began his big comeback on April 17th, 2012.<ul><li> Lots of shows in late March - early April 2016 were like this due Ghost's mic dying and being forced to use a smartphone.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ITakeOffenseToThatLastOne" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ITakeOffenseToThatLastOne">I Take Offense to That Last One!</a>:<ul><li> When accused of being, for example, a "racist, <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Shapeshifter" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Shapeshifter">shapeshifting</a> Jew," his response is "<a class="urllink" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=TUAsAmhfBIw&amp;feature=related">I'm not a Jew!<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a>". Could be considered a running joke.</li><li> A caller sings a parody of "<a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/RudolphTheRedNosedReindeer" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/RudolphTheRedNosedReindeer">Rudolph the Red-Nosed Reindeer</a>" where he calls Ghost a racist, a fruitbowl, a hambone, and a reptile. But Ghost doesn't get offended until he says "Hannukah night", not even noticing that the same line accused him of beating his son.</li><li> A caller once claimed that there's a party at Ghost's house with "free beer, a mountain of cocaine, and girls under 18". Ghost's response is "I don't do cocaine!". Knowing him, one would think he'd react to the "girls under 18" part.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Jerkass" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Jerkass">Jerkass</a>: Ghost himself. One particular example: He went off on a rant about members of <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Music/Slipknot" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Music/Slipknot">Slipknot</a> crying about their bassist's death thus:<div class="indent"> He was a fat idiot! What did they think would happen? ...crying like <em>bitches.</em></div><ul><li> Although the whole reason the show is what it is, the trolls themselves are <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EvilVersusEvil" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EvilVersusEvil">oftentimes not much better than your host himself</a>, with many of the viewers being no less horrible regarding certain groups such as transgender folk or "half-a-tards" as Ghost, and being just as merciless bullies for petty reasons, sometimes even <em>moreso</em>, like the humiliation given to MaskedPony over his harmless kinks due to finding him irritating, to name one incident.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/JerkassHasAPoint" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/JerkassHasAPoint">Jerkass Has a Point</a>:<ul><li> Despite being an <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HairTriggerTemper" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HairTriggerTemper">insane</a>, <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NoIndoorVoice" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NoIndoorVoice">loud</a>, <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SmallNameBigEgo" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SmallNameBigEgo">arrogant</a>, <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Jerkass" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Jerkass">obnoxious asshole</a>, some viewers have found themselves agreeing with some of the things he has to say.<ul><li> Case in point, he actually went on record defending mentally handicapped people as pure beings. Though it's mixed with derogatory terms and the implication that he likes their nature more for the reason that they can do the crappy jobs for cheap and he would later completely take back these compliments after several people with Autism and Asperger Syndrome caused trouble in the Inner Circle.</li></ul></li><li> There would probably be few people who would disagree with Ghost on his contempt for the SOPA and PIPA acts, or Jerry Sandusky. Of course, that doesn't mean that the trolls won't use the latter in order to make him rage...</li><li> He also went on a more detailed rant instead of the "scorched earth" for the whole wildfire jokes and said "People are losing their homes and losing their lives! And you people are laughing!"</li><li> Some of Ghost's rants, despite being filled with a lot of oversimplifications and stereotypes, often have a few good points in them. Occasionally, he can even be down right inspiring. A few random serious callers claimed that they were planning on trolling him to begin with, but couldn't after actually listening to what he has to say.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/JerkWithAHeartOfGold" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/JerkWithAHeartOfGold">Jerk with a Heart of Gold</a>: Ghost to a degree. CelticBrony <em>seemed</em> to be this, but eventually revealed himself to be a <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/JerkWithAHeartOfJerk" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/JerkWithAHeartOfJerk">Jerk with a Heart of Jerk</a>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/KarmaHoudini" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/KarmaHoudini">Karma Houdini</a>: Subverted. CelticBrony's <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EvilPlan" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EvilPlan">Evil Plan</a> succeeded and he got away with it, but his victory was rendered meaningless by the show ending and now he's rejected and hated as the guy who made TCR's first run end.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Kayfabe" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Kayfabe">Kayfabe</a>: No one knows how real some of the more... eccentric... figures on True Capitalist are, or even how real Ghost himself is, but few bother to try and find out, since <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PassThePopcorn" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PassThePopcorn">it's a hell of a lot of fun anyway.</a></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/KickTheDog" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/KickTheDog">Kick the Dog</a>:<ul><li> A literal case: Ghost tells one his listeners that he'll respect him if he kicks his dog on <a class="urllink" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ymfbMcBcVF4&amp;feature=related">27th September 2011<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a>.</li><li> Ghost also does this metaphorically a few times every episode.</li><li> Around Christmas, a legitimate fan bought about $50 in his merchandise and made a video to get a Twitter follow from Ghost and to be in the "True Capitalist Fan Ring of Honor." Instead, Ghost just insulted him and backed down on his word. This event caused many people, legitimate fans and trolls alike, to lose all sympathy for Ghost.</li><li> On January 25th, 2012's episode he declared that all mental disorders from depression to PTSD to autism were entirely fake and basically said that kids suffering from them were "pussies." Whatever sympathy he gained from listeners after his breakdowns were entirely lost after that.<ul><li> This also showcased Ghost as a massive hypocrite as one of his catchphrases during his breakdowns is "I'm jaded man, I mean, I'M DEPRESSED!" So it's okay for him to be depressed?</li></ul></li><li> The May 4th, 2012's broadcast featured Ghost being harsher and nastier than he had been in a long time; <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CharacterDevelopment" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CharacterDevelopment">for the past few months, starting with the Ghostie Awards, he had steadily been evolving into something of a lovable old grouch</a>, so it's somewhat jarring to listen to this broadcast and hear him say that he wants Tub Guy to drown in his bathtub.</li><li> He also gives people's phone numbers away in the hope that their homes will be trolled, generally recognized more of a <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WretchedHive" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WretchedHive">4Chan</a> fighting style than mere kick the doggery.</li><li> On 5/9/12, he said that if <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Music/TupacShakur" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Music/TupacShakur">Tupac Shakur</a> is still alive, he should be killed by other gangsters.<ul><li> From the same episode, during Radio Graffiti, a caller asked Ghost about whatever happened to Xarahox. Ghost replied: "I don't know, hope he killed himself."</li></ul></li><li> Ghost getting extremely angry that the people listening to his show like the Engineer more than him during the <a class="urllink" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=JcsyGcf-GJE">9/20/2016<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a> and <a class="urllink" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Z7U7egvZNzI">9/21/2016<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a> broadcasts. The mixture of <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ItsAllAboutMe" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ItsAllAboutMe">self-pity</a> and <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DisproportionateRetribution" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DisproportionateRetribution">him screeching furiously at the Engineer</a> made him look more like a <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GreenEyedMonster" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GreenEyedMonster">jealous</a> and <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SmugSnake" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SmugSnake">arrogant</a> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheBully" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheBully">bully</a> than the intelligent capitalist he claims to be.</li><li> Ghost's treatment of people who are no longer a part of the Inner Circle class as this, specifically long time callers such as Trumping Capitalist.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/KickTheSonOfABitch" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/KickTheSonOfABitch">Kick the Son of a Bitch</a>: Ghost once doxxed a sex offender, but it wasn't known at the time he was actually a registered sex offender. Rather, it was because of a tasteless Pizzagate joke. The trolls themselves invoked this trope when they followed up on this revealed information after the sex offender admitted to <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/OverusedRunningGag" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/OverusedRunningGag">playing the obnoxious Cleveland calls</a>, only discovering he was a registered sex offender from what they found after the fact.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/KillThePoor" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/KillThePoor">Kill the Poor</a>: <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SubvertedTrope" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SubvertedTrope">Subverted Trope</a>. Ghost suggested that welfare food cards should be replaced with feeding the poor and unemployed with horse meat from put-down horses and wild boars, and he also suggests killing stray cats and dogs for blankets. However, actually killing the homeless <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ImAHumanitarian" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ImAHumanitarian">to use their bodies to feed the poor</a>, as one troll suggests, <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EvenEvilHasStandards" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EvenEvilHasStandards">is crossing the line</a>. That being said, Ghost also once called for replacing welfare with putting the unemployed in "labor camps" instead.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/KissingInATree" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/KissingInATree">Kissing In A Tree</a>: "Ghost and Alex Jones/sitting in a tree/K-I-S-S-I-N-G/first comes fearmongering/then comes gay marriage/then comes <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Metaphorgotten" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Metaphorgotten">my fruity-ass fruitbowl gay son-</a>"</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LargeHam" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LargeHam">Large Ham</a><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/JustForPun" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/JustForPun">bone</a>: When he starts a rant on something, expect lots of hamtastic bellowing, throwing of objects, and threats that would make Brian Blessed proud.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/KnightOfCerebus" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/KnightOfCerebus">Knight of Cerebus</a>: Senator Pooptickler, who is terrifyingly good at doxing people.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LighterAndSofter" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LighterAndSofter">Lighter and Softer</a>: Ghost's occasional "Mr. Optimism" persona is this.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MadnessMantra" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MadnessMantra">Madness Mantra</a>:<ul><li> The "Ban All Bronies" "Fuck Bronies" and "Castrate Bronies" spam callers.</li><li> There was an instance where a caller callled in multiple times simply repeating "Penispenispenispenispenispenis..."</li><li> "SUCK MY DICK" guy, who'll just bellow "SUCK MY DICK" over and over again, occasionally telling Ghost to calm down or pretending to be a regular collar before letting the dick-sucking commence.</li><li> The <a class="urllink" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=o5EsLvSzqGo">"Accident-Prone Kids for Ghost."<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a></li></ul><div class="indent">"Underfed kids, beaten kids, molested kids, lost kids, crying kids, homeless kids, hit and run kids, broken arm kids, broken leg kids!"</div></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MakesSenseInContext" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MakesSenseInContext">Makes Sense In Context</a>: Only on True Capitalist Radio could the sentences <a class="urllink" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=wGnPhoSWW5A">"it's bad enough we got a god damn Pooptickler, but now we got a Pooptickler Jr."<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a> and <a class="urllink" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=aGoxAvu0eN8">"Oh great, we just ran through the generation of Poopticklers"<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a> make sense. The sick-minded and ever-imaginative trolls make for a very long list of such sentences.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ManipulativeEditing" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ManipulativeEditing">Manipulative Editing</a>: It's frighteningly easy to make him rage. Just take one of the following sentences (or for bonus points find something he said in the previous episode), and change <em>x</em> (or a key word in another sentence) to the word of your choice.<div class="indent"> "I happen to have a whole bunch of friends who <em>x</em>/who happen to be <em>x</em>"</div><div class="indent"> "Ghost, from True Capitalist Radio, is a <em>x</em>"</div><div class="indent"> "<em>x</em> sucks the chrome off of a '57 Chevy bumper!"</div><div class="indent"> "I mean, hell, in my personal opinion, <em>x</em> is a good piece of ass.</div><div class="indent"> "Look, what's going on between me and <em>x</em> is personal."</div><div class="indent"> Alternatively, find a sentence where he says "I'm not a goddamn <em>x</em>", and remove "not".</div></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ManOfAThousandVoices" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ManOfAThousandVoices">Man of a Thousand Voices</a>:<ul><li> Ghost has quite a talent with impressions. While most of them are of <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NationalStereotypes" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NationalStereotypes">National Stereotypes</a>, he does perform some of them very well, though <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/OohMeAccentsSlipping" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/OohMeAccentsSlipping">they tend to slip whenever he yells</a>.</li><li> You could listen to his "Optimist voice" and never realize it was him.</li><li> Lampshaded once when a caller said that he would make a great voice actor and then Ghost told him that he already was.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MeaninglessVillainVictory" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MeaninglessVillainVictory">Meaningless Villain Victory</a>: Sure, Celtic's gambit might have worked, but Ghost's retirement made the whole thing moot, and ensured that even if he achieved his goal of being 'famous' for it (which doesn't seem likely), he would be remembered as <img src="/images/article-hreficon-ymmv.png" class="ymmv1 rounded" title="This example contains a YMMV entry. It should be moved to the YMMV tab."><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/StopHavingFunGuys" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/StopHavingFunGuys">that dick who ended TCR.</a></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MistakenForGay" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MistakenForGay">Mistaken for Gay</a>: Since Ghost is a homophobe, trolls are very dedicated to making him sound as gay as possible in their splices.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MistakenForRacist" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MistakenForRacist">Mistaken for Racist</a>: Subverted. Ghost insists that this is what's happened to him, but his usage of terms like "Alabama black snake," and firm belief in racial stereotypes reveals a very different story.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MistakenIdentity" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MistakenIdentity">Mistaken Identity</a>: Someone <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BullyingADragon" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BullyingADragon">prank-called</a> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DidYouJustPunchOutCthulhu" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DidYouJustPunchOutCthulhu">the FBI</a> with splices of Ghost's voice, and as a result he sounds completely, hilariously insane:<div class="indent"> <strong>FBI:</strong> Hello, this is the FBI.</div><div class="indent"> <strong>Ghost:</strong> Is this Nikolai?!</div><div class="indent"> <strong>FBI:</strong> ...no, this is the FBI.</div><div class="indent"> <strong>Ghost:</strong> You cock-eyed Russian.</div></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Mondegreen" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Mondegreen">Mondegreen</a>:<ul><li> In the November 1 Radio Graffiti segment, <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/KiraBuckland" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/KiraBuckland">Kira Buckland</a> calls in as <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/MyLittlePonyFriendshipIsMagic" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/MyLittlePonyFriendshipIsMagic">Twilight Sparkle</a> and says "suck my flank" to imitate the "suck my dick" guy. Ghost mishears it and says "Are you kidding me?! Suck my BLANK?!"</li><li> Ghost misheard Tri$ha saying "what do you have against the <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Transgender" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Transgender">third gender</a>" as "surf dinner", to which he replied "I <em>like</em> Surf 'n' Turf, what the hell you talking about?"</li><li> Ghost has misinterpreted the word "<a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/Touhou" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/Touhou">Touhou</a>" as "<a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BlindIdiotTranslation" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BlindIdiotTranslation">toe hoe</a>" on several occasions, causing him to rant that the fandom is made up of "sick foot fetish freaks".</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MotorMouth" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MotorMouth">Motor Mouth</a>:<ul><li> Ghost. He can literally talk for hours.</li><li> Some of the callers are this, because they have to fit whatever they're trying to enrage Ghost with into a few seconds so he doesn't hang up on him. The "Suck my dick" guy in particular can talk very fast when he isn't bellowing his catchphrase.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MundaneMadeAwesome" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MundaneMadeAwesome">Mundane Made Awesome</a>: "I'm implementing CHATROOM MARTIAL LAWWWWWWWWWWWWWWWWWWWWW! YEAH HA HAAAAAAA~"</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NationalStereotypes" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NationalStereotypes">National Stereotypes</a>: In his "Guess the Minority" game, Ghost tries to identify the race of the caller by asking questions relating to these (i.e. "What is your favorite food?")</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NeverMyFault" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NeverMyFault">Never My Fault</a>: Ghost will blame anyone but himself for his mistakes that makes on the show, even if he was the one who made the mistake to begin with.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NoTrueScotsman" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NoTrueScotsman">No True Scotsman</a>: Common method of trolling early in the show involves trolls tweeting/spamming in the chat to Ghost that he's un-American due to his dislike of coffee. This often leads into him <a class="urllink" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=OpGfyENXwbw">going on a long rant about coffee drinkers and the fact that coffee is not produced in United States<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NoHonorAmongThieves" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NoHonorAmongThieves">No Honor Among Thieves</a>: Ghost's inner circle, <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HorribleJudgeOfCharacter" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HorribleJudgeOfCharacter">who he considered to be his true friends</a>, all turned on him in a hilarious call during the <a class="urllink" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=rNWU72pI6bQ">October 3rd, 2016 broadcast<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a> where they endorsed the Engineer over him. Even <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SycophanticServant" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SycophanticServant">Teutonic Plague</a>, who's normally a huge brown-noser, took part in mocking Ghost.<ul><li> This did a complete 180 when Ghost purged several of his Inner Circle during the months of May and June.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NoIndoorVoice" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NoIndoorVoice">No Indoor Voice</a>: When he's angry, Ghost will raise his voice. A lot.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NonSequitur" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NonSequitur">Non Sequitur</a>: Most "troll" calls end up being like this: Host brings up topic. Host asks for opinion on topic. Caller says something completely off-topic. Host makes fun of him and/or rages about off-topic call. That's the circle of life around here.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ObfuscatingStupidity" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ObfuscatingStupidity">Obfuscating Stupidity</a>: The Engineer seems like a buffoon but he shows several times that he's smarter than he seems.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/OhCrap" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/OhCrap">Oh, Crap!</a>: His reaction to the police (<a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/UnreliableNarrator" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/UnreliableNarrator">supposedly</a>) setting up outside his home and knocking on his door while on air;<div class="indent"> <strong>Ghost</strong>: <em>Jesus Christ... the hell is going on here?</em> [Police knocking] <em>Oh shit! AW CHRIST, AW CHRIST NO! GET AWAY! <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TooDumbToLive" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TooDumbToLive">GET AWAY I'M ARMED</a>, GET AWAY!</em></div></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/OlderThanTheyThink" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/OlderThanTheyThink">Older Than They Think</a> (<a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/InUniverse" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/InUniverse">In-Universe</a>): Before it turned into Engineer's running gag, someone played the theme from <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/BossNigger" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/BossNigger">that film</a> during the <a class="urllink" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=u2msR5g817Y&amp;t=7m52s">June 17th, 2011 raid<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/OnceAnEpisode" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/OnceAnEpisode">Once an Episode</a>: He always starts with the markets, then Twitter shoutouts, then goes to political news, and finally Radio Graffiti, a call-in segment where callers get "three to four seconds to say whatever's on your mind"<ul><li> During the two hour show period between March and September of 2016, the markets were notably absent, with Ghost discussing news right off the bat. As of February 2017, a new "cryptocurrency" segment has been added before the markets.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/OneHitKill" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/OneHitKill">One-Hit Kill</a>: Coodoo17 made this into an art, often taking down Ghost with a single remix in 2012 and the early episodes of Ghost's 2016 return. Tub Guy seems to have taken the mantle, because every time he called in from July 2016 onward, he usually caused Ghost to end the show in rage.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/OpeningNarration" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/OpeningNarration">Opening Narration</a>: Near the top of the hour, but always to the effect of "This is the (second/third and final) hour of the True Capitalist Radio broadcast, I am your host, the man they call Ghost."</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/OverlyLongGag" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/OverlyLongGag">Overly Long Gag</a>:<ul><li> On December 14th, when Engineer hijacked the show, <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AwesomeMcCoolname" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AwesomeMcCoolname">Knee Slappington</a>, AKA the Austin Vibrator, called in with his usual "OoOoOoOoOoO" sound effect. <a class="urllink" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=43u4tE1wokg&amp;t=407">Rather than cutting him off, Engineer let it run for several minutes, even trying to sing along at points.<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a></li></ul><div class="indent"><strong>Knee Slappington:</strong> OoOoOoOoOoOoOoOoOoOoOoOoOoOoOoOoOoOoOoOoOoOoOoOoOoOoOoOoOoOoOoOoOoOoOoOoOoOoOoOoOoOoOoOoOoO</div><div class="indent"><strong>Engineer:</strong> BAP BAP BAP AWWWWWWWW</div><ul><li> This ended when Engineer broke down <img src="/images/article-hreficon-ymmv.png" class="ymmv1 rounded" title="This example contains a YMMV entry. It should be moved to the YMMV tab."><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheWoobie" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheWoobie">and cried.</a></li><li> An extended version of "Twitter Shootouts" by J-Man ran for almost 4 minutes, and half of that footage consumed the rest of Ghost's Radio Graffiti time on <a class="urllink" href="https://youtu.be/s7dma-ZExrE?t=14m20s">February 27th, 2017<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a>, leaving Ghost enraged and unable to advertise his show at the end. The entirety of the splice was <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ExactlyWhatItSaysOnTheTin" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ExactlyWhatItSaysOnTheTin">Ghost calling out the names of everyone he shoots dead</a>.</li><li> Other splices have also reached this long ever since Ghost began the Saturday Night Troll Show.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/OverusedRunningGag" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/OverusedRunningGag">Overused Running Gag</a>: Twitter users continuously made-up names referencing the Texas fire, India and Turkey quakes, and Steve Jobs' death for a time.<ul><li> Early post-return had Big Jack and Daniel Bryan Splices take this mantle up. Due to their overuse, people got annoyed at how frequently they showed up.</li><li> The Cleveland calls are widely agreed to be this, popping up frequently throughout the show and doing nothing but cause annoyance for Ghost and the trolls alike.</li><li> As of 2018, Ghost reads shoutout names that trick him to saying racial terms far more than he should have. And on most occasions, he catches on too late and flips out over it.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/OOCIsSeriousBusiness" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/OOCIsSeriousBusiness">OOC Is Serious Business</a>: When G was apparently threatening to kill himself, Ghost dropped the act of being mad at him over "the betrayal" and tried to talk him down from it. When it turned out that he was lying to promote his show, Ghost got mad for real, going so far as threatening to end TCR forever.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PapaWolf" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PapaWolf">Papa Wolf</a>: Don't insult his family, especially his grandmother.<div class="indent"><strong>Ghost:</strong> DON'T YOU EVER TALK ABOUT MAH FAMILY!</div></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ParodyCommercial" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ParodyCommercial">Parody Commercials</a>: Throughout the show's history, there have been trolls posing as ads for fake products.<ul><li> One of the most well-remembered ads was for <a class="urllink" href="https://youtu.be/OG0Qt_uZwPU?t=18m51s">Karaszkun Burgers<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a>, a fictional restaurant owned by Karaszkun.</li><li> True Capitalist Radio Greatest Hits purportedly contained all the Ghost remixes of the day. This idea is sometimes repeated with newer remixes or taken in a more literal direction.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PetTheDog" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PetTheDog">Pet the Dog</a>:<ul><li> On January 6th, 2012, Ghost defends Equestrian Citizen from racial slurs.</li><li> Despite his conflicting feelings toward the Engineer and his antics, Ghost has defended him when callers accused him of being 'retarded' or 'incompetent'.</li><li> Despite his well known feelings towards the LGBT community, he openly criticized Chick-fil-A on his Twitter concerning their support of bigoted groups and told the restaurant to <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/StayInTheKitchen" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/StayInTheKitchen">Get Back in the Kitchen</a> make them some chicken.</li><li> While he shows disgust towards the "trans-testicles" who call in, he does usually use their preferred pronouns when referring to them and has a much higher opinion of them than homosexuals and lesbians whom he views as <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AllGaysArePromiscuous" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AllGaysArePromiscuous">being overtly promiscuous</a>. Ghost has stated that his positive opinion of transgender people is based on him having talked to a lot of them and believing that they want to just live out a normal life and marry a heterosexual male, instead of <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HeteronormativeCrusader" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HeteronormativeCrusader">lowering themselves into promiscuous activity like homosexuals</a>.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PleaseSubscribeToOurChannel" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PleaseSubscribeToOurChannel">Please Subscribe to Our Channel</a>: "<a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CatchPhrase" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CatchPhrase">Spread it around LIKE WAHLDFAUR!</a>"</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PoesLaw" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PoesLaw">Poe's Law</a>:<ul><li> Is he a true capitalist, or a talented voice actor and the world's greatest professional troll? He demonstrates his voice acting talents on many occasions and is just <em>too</em> perfect a trolling material. You'd think he'd learned by now not to answer calls from Dr. Pooptickler.</li><li> Does Ghost have a genuine mental condition or is he just entertaining his listeners with his various episodes of <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheParanoiac" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheParanoiac">paranoia</a> on the show? Once again, his talent as an actor makes this almost impossible to tell at times.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PointAndLaughShow" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PointAndLaughShow">Point-and-Laugh Show</a>: A rare case of this trope where it's the <em>host</em> that's being laughed and pointed at.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PrecisionFStrike" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PrecisionFStrike">Precision F-Strike</a>: When Ghost is really, <em>really</em>, angry, he will fire one off. This is also one of the few intelligible words the Engineer can say.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ProductPlacement" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ProductPlacement">Product Placement</a>: He really hates people trying to get free promotion on his show; most famously the Surge Radio guy, and during the final weeks of the show's original, trolls also played advertisements during Radio Graffiti.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PutOnABus" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PutOnABus">Put on a Bus</a>: DarkRazorZ is deployed in Japan and not around to upload videos.<ul><li> Several 2012 callers have fallen victim to this since the Return, due to them moving on with life, most notably Ghetto Capitalist and <a class="createlink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NavyHuskie" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NavyHuskie">Navy Huskie</a>.</li><li> Along with Skype callers, some of the once-frequent 2016 callers have fallen into this as well, such as 8Equal, the Arab Prince, and African Booty Scratcher. Though with ABS he still makes appearances in other trolls' calls.</li></ul></li></ul></div><div class="folderlabel" onclick="togglefolder('folder3');">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;R-Z&nbsp;</div><div id="folder3" class="folder" isfolder="true" style="display:block;"><ul><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RantInducingSlight" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RantInducingSlight">Rant-Inducing Slight</a>: After a host of voice clips Ghost weathered with simple 'shut up's, an apparent child asking for anal sex finally tips him over the edge.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RageQuit" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RageQuit">Rage Quit</a>: Ghost seems to be the master at faking going off the air, since usually something will end up happening which turns it into more of an intermission. However, on at least <strong>nineteen</strong> separate occasions, he <em>has</em> truly ended the show prematurely:<ul><li> The first known ragequit was on April 26th, 2011, when the Internet Buttstalker somehow pulled off 10 calls in a row.</li><li> The second known ragequit was on May 10, 2011, after Ghost got very annoyed to the point where he flipped out.</li><li> The third known ragequit was on July 8, 2011, when people claimed they were bored and he sang Nyan Cat.</li><li> The fourth known ragequit was on August 1, 2011, when people were greatly annoying him on his first day back from a hiatus (the last one was a homosexual that pretended he was a fan of the show).</li><li> The fifth known ragequit was on August 19, 2011, after a caller claimed he was going to make a game based off his show.</li><li> The sixth known ragequit was on August 29, 2011 after an audio splice about him being the king of 10-year old boy ass.</li><li> The seventh was two days later on August 31, 2011 after the "Money, Success, Fame, Bronies" call. He did sort of come back to dance to the Mexican Hat Dance, but truly rage quit after that.</li><li> The eighth known ragequit was on September 7, 2011, when a caller played a splice of Ghost using the N-word, followed by Ghost calling him back only to receive the same audio splice. Ghost <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DisproportionateRetribution" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DisproportionateRetribution">gave the troll's number out on-air, demanded that his listeners send 20,000 pizzas to his home</a>, and then left.</li><li> The ninth was on September 9, 2011. Ghost was already infuriated to the tipping point by the "Texas en Fuego" twitter name, and back-to-back remixes of "<em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/Tetris" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/Tetris">Tetris</a></em> Theme A" pushed him past it.</li><li> The tenth was on November 8, 2011, after the hambone remix of <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Music/Skrillex" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Music/Skrillex">Skrillex</a>'s Scary Monsters and Nice Sprites.</li><li> The eleventh was on December 7, 2011 after he considered the fruitiness level to be way outside his comfort zone; he first did a fake ragequit after someone sang a song about him, calling him a "Jewish hambone faggot brony", then, later in the show, he finally ragequit after Note Party/Tri$ha called him a hambone in response to a comment about estrogen pills.</li><li> The twelfth was on January 6th, 2012, after reading a chatroom name saying "Mug Ranny's A Tranny"<span class="notelabel" onclick="togglenote('note570xc');"><sup>note&nbsp;</sup></span><span id="note570xc" class="inlinefolder" isnote="true" onclick="togglenote('note570xc');" style="cursor:pointer;font-size:smaller;display:none;">"My Granny's A Tranny"</span></li><li> The thirteenth was on January 25th, 2012, during Radio Graffiti, after someone called another radio show using Ghost's voice, and the host of the radio show that was pranked said "he sounds like, uh, what's his name, Alex Jones", which sent Ghost into a massive rage about being compared to Alex Jones.</li><li> The fourteenth was on February 9th, 2012, with the "SUCK MAH DICK" guy singing a <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Music/BrunoMars" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Music/BrunoMars">Bruno Mars</a> parody, followed shortly by Tub Guy calling in to say that he was going to "invite Ghost to his World War III bunker for a three-way with Alex Jones"</li><li> The fifteenth was on February 16th, 2012 after two "<a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/VerbalTic" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/VerbalTic">trans</a>-<a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/YouKeepUsingThatWord" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/YouKeepUsingThatWord">testicles</a>" "fought" over him, not long after he went into a massive rage over a <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/FamilyGuy" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/FamilyGuy">Herbert the Pervert</a> call.</li><li> The sixteenth was on March 2nd, 2012, after a caller played an autotuned version of Pinkie Pie's Laughter Song.</li><li> The seventeenth was on April 19, 2012, after the <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/BobTheBuilder" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/BobTheBuilder">Bob the Builder</a> remix by Coodoo17.</li><li> The eighteenth was on April 30th, 2012, after a back to back combo of a prank call of Ghost calling PETA and TexasStroll playing a remix of Ghost singing Stevie B's "Spring Love."</li><li> The nineteenth and last time was on May 15, 2012, after a back to back combo of a fake advertisement disrespecting KaraszKun and Coodoo17 playing a <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Music/BackstreetBoys" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Music/BackstreetBoys">Backstreet Boys</a> remix.</li><li> This was also subverted at least three times: The first known occasion was on May 18, 2011, when Ghost was doing a news story and when he was doing calls and the feed unexpectedly died around 160 minutes into the show. It then played the outro a few seconds later. The second time was on January 27th, 2012's Radio Graffiti segment; someone played a clip of himself allegedly playing a Ghost clip at <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Radio/TheHowardSternShow" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Radio/TheHowardSternShow">The Howard Stern Show</a></em>, right at the end of the show. While in reality, he got cut off by BlogTalkRadio suddenly removing the functionality that let his show overrun, the amount of reaction you heard from him before he got cut off was probably enough to leave you believing that he was having a mega-rage and just decided to cut himself off because he didn't want to go on after that. The third instance was on April 17th, 2012's episode during Radio Graffiti when the microphone died <em>twice</em> during the segment. The first time it was after the sixth caller, then it died again for the rest of the show fifteen minutes after Radio Graffiti started. He also faked it twice in December only for the Engineer to hijack the show until his return.</li><li> Every single episode from October 3rd 2016 to his surprise sunday broadcast for the 2nd Presidential debate, Ghost ended shows really early when ever a Creator's Pet of his gets outed by Trolls as liking or doing something Ghost disagrees with (G liking Anime, Karaszkun drawing pornography, and Teutonic Plague endorsing Team Engineer). He often exited with a guttural roar in rage.</li><li> Whenever something dramatic with the Trump administration happens, this generally occurs. Ghost rage quit on the January 27th show due to Richard Spencer supposedly being a Russian plant, and on Valentine's Day due to Michael T. Flynn resigning after possible links to Russia.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RatedMForManly" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RatedMForManly">Rated M for Manly</a>: Ghost certainly thinks he's this, making empty threats to the trolls and how he's a big badass. He also screams for fruitbowls and bronies to have 'testosterone shot up their ass'. He also expects his callers to sound similarly manly.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RecurringRiff" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RecurringRiff">Recurring Riff</a>:<ul><li> "Well you know what this country is turning into? Junkyard America!"</li><li> Sometimes after calls that <em>really</em> grind his gears, he'll do a musical intermission while he cools off. Sometimes he does an intermission in such a way that will force the trolls to turn him off by boring them to death, because they apparently love "lulz" and "fruitbowl music"</li><li> MONEY, SUCCESS, FAME, GLAMOUR.<ul><li> MONEY, SUCCESS, FAME, BRONIES. ("YOU MADE A SONG OF THAT?!?!?!")</li></ul></li><li> "Fuck You Texas" and "Melting Pot of Alcohol".</li><li> Whenever Ghost lies, expect someone to point it out with <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Music/FleetwoodMac" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Music/FleetwoodMac">Little Lies</a> or <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/SonicTheHedgehog" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/SonicTheHedgehog">Sonic the Hedgehog's</a> Game Over music.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RefrainFromAssuming" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RefrainFromAssuming">Refrain from Assuming</a>:<ul><li> Ghost often gets song titles or genres wrong after hearing remixes. He's referred to Brodyquest as both "<a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/BeverlyHillsCop" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/BeverlyHillsCop">Axel F</a>" and the theme to <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/Footloose" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/Footloose">Footloose</a>, the Dr. Mario theme as "circus music", "Entrance of the Gladiators" (a song which <em>is</em> often circus music) as "hoedown music", both the <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/PokemonBlackAndWhite" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/PokemonBlackAndWhite">Driftveil City theme</a> and "She Blinded Me With Science" as "that weird science song", a remix of <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/MegaMan3" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/MegaMan3">Spark Man's</a> theme as <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/Contra" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/Contra">Contra</a>, The <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/UsefulNotes/NintendoGameCube" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/UsefulNotes/NintendoGameCube">Nintendo GameCube</a> boot remix as <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Music/MichaelJackson" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Music/MichaelJackson">Wanna Be Startin' Somethin'</a>, <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/DawnOfTheDead1978" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/DawnOfTheDead1978">"The Gonk"</a> as "music from <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheRoaringTwenties" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheRoaringTwenties">The Roaring '20s</a>", <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/BeautyAndTheBeast" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/BeautyAndTheBeast">"Be Our Guest"</a> as poetry, and <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/TheLegendOfZeldaOcarinaOfTime" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/TheLegendOfZeldaOcarinaOfTime">The Song of Storms</a> as a song from Yoshi (this one made DarkRazorZ rage).</li><li> A frequent Skype caller with the username "<a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/TaraStrong" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/TaraStrong">Tara Strong</a>" often plays spliced quotes from everypony's favorite show, but has also played <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/DrawnTogether" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/DrawnTogether">Princess Clara</a> lines, taking advantage of the fact that she shares the same voice actor as Twilight Sparkle. Ghost caught on to the part that mattered, and immediately dismissed them as being Pony-related.</li><li> Averted when someone was playing "<a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Franchise/Castlevania" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Franchise/Castlevania">Bloody Tears</a>" and Ghost thought it was Mexican music, until he heard a little more and realized it was from <em>Castlevania</em>.</li><li> There was a caller on August 9, 2016's episode who played random clips from <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/DOTA2" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/DOTA2">DOTA 2</a></em> competitions that Ghost thought was baseball.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RepurposedPopSong" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RepurposedPopSong">Repurposed Pop Song</a>: The <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/SanfordAndSon" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/SanfordAndSon">Sanford and Son</a></em> theme for the Junkyard America song, and the theme from <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/ThePriceIsRight" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/ThePriceIsRight">The Price Is Right</a></em> for Guess the Minority.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ReverseCerebusSyndrome" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ReverseCerebusSyndrome">Reverse Cerebus Syndrome</a>: As time went on, there were more and more trolls and fewer (supposedly) serious listeners, to the point where by the last episodes almost no one seemed to take Ghost seriously any more. Also on a micro scale in each episode: the Markets and News are generally standard political/financial-show fare, but when Ghost starts the calls, shout outs, and radio graffiti, things quickly get silly.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RiddleForTheAges" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RiddleForTheAges">Riddle for the Ages</a>: Is Ghost a real person, or just a troll? No one knows for certain (and probably never will now) but <img src="/images/article-hreficon-ymmv.png" class="ymmv1 rounded" title="This example contains a YMMV entry. It should be moved to the YMMV tab."><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MST3KMantra" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MST3KMantra">few actually care</a>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RippedFromTheHeadlines" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RippedFromTheHeadlines">Ripped from the Headlines</a>: A lot of people like to troll Ghost by making Twitter names referencing (at the time) recent events, typically in a derogatory fashion.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RoguesGallery" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RoguesGallery">Rogues Gallery</a>: Let's see: the trolls on Radio Graffiti are composed of a guy who pretty much lives in a bathtub, a stereotypical African-American man who uses welfare fraud schemes to capitalize "the ghetto way", numerous trans- and homosexuals who want to have sex with Ghost, bronies as well as actual ponies from <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/MyLittlePonyFriendshipIsMagic" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/MyLittlePonyFriendshipIsMagic">the show</a>, an African man who likes to read erotic Anne Frank fanfiction, a guy whom Ghost genuinely liked until finding out about his diaper fetish My Little Pony fanfics, a guy who keeps drinking his own urine over and over again, a former McDonalds mascot and current white supremacist rapper with a moon for a head, a sick twisted version of <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/TheMuppetShow" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/TheMuppetShow">Kermit The Frog</a> who wants to have sex with him and <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AnythingThatMoves" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AnythingThatMoves">various other things</a>, and the list goes on and on.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RuleOfThree" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RuleOfThree">Rule of Three</a>: As a general rule, Ghost would go into cans.wav after three trolls called in talking about the same subject material, e.g. calling him Alex Jones.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RunningGag" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RunningGag">Running Gag</a>: Many:<ul><li> "Guess the Minority", a segment where Ghost tries to guess the ethnicity of a caller by asking them questions related to stereotypes, or guessing based off their voice alone. He <a class="urllink" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2mPUJTjmgD4">freakin' loves this game, man!<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a></li><li> Spontaneously breaking into song (Junkyard America!)</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Website/Twitter" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Website/Twitter">Twitter</a> filled with usernames intended to make him rage ("PoopTickler?! What kind of a name is PoopTickler?!").<ul><li> Twitter names taking the form of "_______ for ______" (i.e. Spongies for Ghost, Bronies for Ghost, <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DudeNotFunny" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DudeNotFunny">Radiation for Japan,</a> etc.)</li><li> Twitter names combining Ghost's name with that of communist or fascist dictators (i.e. Ghostler, Benito Ghostini, Ghostef Stalin, Fidel Ghostro, etc.)</li><li> Twitter/Gab names that stick a pair of balls on objects or people and call them "Trans ____".</li><li> Transexual Gab names that rhyme (i.e. Slag with a Meatbag, Dolls with Balls, Nanas with Bananas, etc.)</li></ul></li><li> Ghost playing clips from "representatives" from various foreign locales (including "Mr. Fortune Cookie" from Communist China, Machmud, a "representative of the Libyan rebel faction", and "The Guru", a stereotypical Indian)</li><li> NIKOLAI 2012</li><li> Ghost's disdain for the Occupy Wall Street movement has led to a series of trolls and twitter names mocking him for it. Among them are OccupyCanadia, OccupyManehattan, OccupyCanterlot, OccupyPonyville, OccupySixthStreet, and <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BreadEggsMilkSquick" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BreadEggsMilkSquick">OccupyGhost'sAss.</a></li><li> There was a recurring joke throughout the January 20th show that Ghost was every member of the Today Show.</li><li> Every time he tries to calm himself down through meditation, he'll end up tossing cans after sighting "that freakin' panda". <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ItMakesJustAsMuchSenseInContext" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ItMakesJustAsMuchSenseInContext">No, it does NOT make sense in context.</a></li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SatanIsGood" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SatanIsGood">Satan is Good</a>:<div class="indent"><strong>Ghost</strong>: <a class="urllink" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=8jkQrvwQm-M">Satan is good, Satan is my pal<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a>!</div></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SayMyName" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SayMyName">Say My Name</a>: "DAMN YOU NAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAVYYYYYY HUUUUUUUUUUUUUUUUUUUUUSSKIIIIIIIIIIIIIIIEEEEEE...!"</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ScoringPoints" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ScoringPoints">Scoring Points</a>: Each episode's score is measured by how many times cans.wav occurs. <a class="urllink" href="https://truecapitalist.miraheze.org/wiki/Cans_High_Score">The top 10 high scores are kept here.<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SdrawkcabName" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SdrawkcabName">Sdrawkcab Name</a>: One caller claimed to be Ohsa, the backwards Asho.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SensoryAbuse" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SensoryAbuse">Sensory Abuse</a>: Some trolls like to ear-rape Ghost (and the audience) by playing <em>very</em> loud buzzers or yelling at the mic. They tend to be cluster calls, too.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SeriesFauxnale" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SeriesFauxnale">Series Fauxnale</a>: Many episodes throughout TCR's history seemed to be the end, either with Ghost vowing to not return or events immediately after putting the show's future in doubt.<ul><li> April 1st, 2011 was the first of these, with Ghost stating that show would be the end after a prominent fan of his was outed for being a pedophile.</li><li> May 15th 2012 was the last episode until March 2016 due to the hacking of Ghost's twitter account a week later, and his announcement the day after that the show was over.</li><li> May 6th 2017 was followed by a long break from the show, with many losing hope, however Ghost eventually returned on October 31st.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SeriousBusiness" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SeriousBusiness">Serious Business</a>: Ghost thinks his show is this. Most of his audience seems to think otherwise.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SesquipedalianLoquaciousness" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SesquipedalianLoquaciousness">Sesquipedalian Loquaciousness</a>: Ghost showed traces of this during some of his shows.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ShoutOut" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ShoutOut">Shout-Out</a>: Many troll calls, but also Ghost himself on occasion:<ul><li> <a class="urllink" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Ku2G1ljsryg">Mmmmmmmagnets, how do they work, magnets, magnets, BAAAAAAAAAAAHHHH BAAAHHHH<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a></li><li> Ghost once did an impression of a stumbling-mumbling troll as "<a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/TheGrimAdventuresOfBillyAndMandy" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/TheGrimAdventuresOfBillyAndMandy">My name is Billy. My favorite number's zero. My favorite color's clear. My favorite subject's lunch.</a>"</li><li> One troll called with a clip of <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/UsefulNotes/RonaldReagan" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/UsefulNotes/RonaldReagan">Ronald Reagan</a> <span class="notelabel" onclick="togglenote('note6hsy5');"><sup>note&nbsp;</sup></span><span id="note6hsy5" class="inlinefolder" isnote="true" onclick="togglenote('note6hsy5');" style="cursor:pointer;font-size:smaller;display:none;">Specifically, "Tear down this wall" </span>. Ghost's response? "<a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/BackToTheFuture" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/BackToTheFuture">Ronald Reagan? The actor?"</a></li><li> In some pre-return cluster calls, he said <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/Portal" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/Portal">APERTURE SCIENCE!</a> to drown out the fail-trolls.</li><li> 4/20/12 has Ghost commenting on how apprehensive he is to consume weed, <img src="/images/article-hreficon-ymmv.png" class="ymmv1 rounded" title="This example contains a YMMV entry. It should be moved to the YMMV tab."><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CriticalResearchFailure" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CriticalResearchFailure">citing</a> <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/ReeferMadness" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/ReeferMadness">Reefer Madness</a></em>.</li><li> On Episode 223 of True Capitalist Radio, he tells Tub Guy to take a <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/GroundhogDay" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/GroundhogDay">bath with a toaster</a>. Interestingly, this wasn't the first shout-out to <em>Groundhog Day</em> he made throughout the show's history.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ShowWithinAShow" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ShowWithinAShow">Show Within a Show</a>: True Optimist Radio, created in response to a <a class="urllink" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_Ie0VxwSFN8">caller<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a> that Ghost declared wanted everything sugar-coded with optimism, turning one of his mocking voices into a new persona, Mr. Optimism, who tries to conduct the show in a <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LighterAndSofter" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LighterAndSofter">Lighter and Softer</a> manner.<ul><li> J-Man Capitalist once aired a fake radio-graffiti segment <em>within the actual Radio Graffiti</em> that was able to fit every troll caller, plus the Cleveland Caller (<a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RefugeinAudacity" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RefugeinAudacity">represented by chimp noises</a>), into a 60 second splice.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ShutUpKirk" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ShutUpKirk">Shut Up, Kirk!</a>: When someone infuriates him in a call, he will tell them to shut up and call them out. One example was on February 3, 2012's Radio Graffiti segment, where a caller just tells him how to run his show. Ghost did <strong><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/UnstoppableRage" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/UnstoppableRage">not</a></strong> take it well and called him out for being "a Roman Polanski pedophile."</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SitcomArchNemesis" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SitcomArchNemesis">Sitcom Arch-Nemesis</a>: The Internet Buttstalker, Tzeki, Alex Jones, Howard Stern, <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TroublingUnchildlikeBehavior" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TroublingUnchildlikeBehavior">Asho</a>, the Ghetto Capitalist, DarkRazorZ, Equestrian Citizen, Tri$ha, NavyHuskie, Coodoo17, the African Booty Scratcher, and many more.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SlashFic" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SlashFic">Slash Fic</a>: <a class="urllink" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gSzND65vhvM">This<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SmallNameBigEgo" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SmallNameBigEgo">Small Name, Big Ego</a>:<ul><li> Ghost has been this for a while, but it shows the most on the episode on 8/29/11. He actually believes that he is more significant to pop culture than 4chan, and says that he's making a mask for Ghost, and actually thinks it's going to overshadow the <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/VForVendetta" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/VForVendetta">Guy Fawkes mask</a>.</li><li> He repeatedly claims that he is "listened to by tens of thousands of capitalists THROUGHOUT THE WORLD!!"</li><li> On 12/12/11, he actually states the possibility of a Ghostcon and said he had a band who "will be at the Grammies."</li><li> In response to people requesting the Engineer to host again: "<em>I'm</em> the talent!"</li><li> Ghost actually believed that Alex Jones was listening to his broadcasts (<a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NoIndoorVoice" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NoIndoorVoice">"I KNOW YOU'RE LISTENING, ALEX!! YOU FAT, POT-BELLIED BASTARD!"</a>) on a regular basis in order to steal ideas such as Radio Graffiti from him.<ul><li> On March 9, 2018, Ghost declared war on him after mistaking a splice of him for the real thing.</li><li> Surprisingly enough, though, <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheCuckoolanderWasRight" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheCuckoolanderWasRight">he did actually get this at least somewhat right</a>, as Alex admitted <a class="urllink" href="http://imgur.com/vUXYIol">that he had listened to some of the older episodes<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a>. Whether he rips off Ghost or not is a little more questionable.</li></ul></li><li> On January 9, 2012's episode, after he read the chatroom name "4 Years of Shitty Radio" in the Chatroom Shout-Outs segment, he claimed that he is an internet legend.</li><li> It's only gotten worse after the revival. When people started remixing his intro, he claimed that it's the "greatest intro in radio today"</li><li> Approaching his 500th overall episode (including Conservative Radio), he started screaming that he belongs in the "Internet Hall of Fame".</li><li> He claims to be in tight with the Trump administration and Trump's associates, including his former campaign manager Roger Stone.</li><li> On the Ghost Show Episode 13, he claims he will be the best competitive gamer who's ever walked on the face of the earth.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheSocialDarwinist" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheSocialDarwinist">The Social Darwinist</a>: Ghost believes that human progress would be brought about by the elimination of individuals who cannot sustain themselves. He believes that humans should be applied to natural selection so that only the working class, A.K.A., the ones who can sustain themselves, should be the only ones to live. Ghost has also stated that he is "pro-death" in general, approves of Rick Perry's record number of executions and approves of people ignoring safety laws simply because it would be more likely for them to get killed in an accident.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SomeOfMyBestFriendsAreX" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SomeOfMyBestFriendsAreX">Some of My Best Friends Are X</a>: "I happen to have a whole <em>bunch</em> of friends who <em>happen</em> to be black!" Or Mexican, or women, <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DiggingYourselfDeeper" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DiggingYourselfDeeper">or "Wops", or "Camel Jockeys"</a>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SpinOff" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SpinOff">Spin-Off</a>: In a way; both Goofy_Bone (most infamously), and Asho, also had their own shows on BlogTalkRadio. The usual trolls started targeting Goofy_Bone's show too. Despite trying to defend himself, he ended up caving in and doing his own version of Radio Graffiti. This continued over a slight hiatus Ghost had, but when he was alerted to this, he, predictably, <a class="urllink" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=rgrmf3JlsM4">called Goofy out and went off about it<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a>, as usual. He dubbed it a "poor man's Mexican version" and a "<a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/YouKeepUsingThatWord" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/YouKeepUsingThatWord">bean and cheese</a>" version of his own show. Then in response, <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AppropriatedAppelation" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AppropriatedAppelation">Goofy re-named it Bean and Cheese Graffiti</a>.<ul><li> An actual one for the show comes in the form of the Saturday Night Troll Show. A separate broadcast dedicated to, you guessed it, trolling Ghost.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SpringtimeForHitler" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SpringtimeForHitler">Springtime for</a> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/JustForPun" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/JustForPun">Ghostler</a>: If one assumes the Engineer is just a persona used by Ghost. Following another fake <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Ragequit" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Ragequit">ragequit</a>, the Engineer takes over the show, playing songs disliked by Ghost and answering calls in his unintelligible gibberish. Ghost eventually 'returns' and proceeds to scold the Engineer. It seems like he did this in an attempt to either chastise the listeners or convince the trolls that the show had effectively ended, but when he got back and started taking calls, people were demanding that the Engineer host the show again. This has turned into a surprisingly effective trolling tactic, causing Ghost to enter fits of envious rage over <em>his own character.</em></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/StayInTheKitchen" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/StayInTheKitchen">Stay in the Kitchen</a>: Whenever a woman comes on who calls him out on his downfalls, attempts legitimate arguing, or trolls him, expect this to be his response.<ul><li> Interestingly he seems to be completely unaware of how this Trope is sexist. When people started accusing him for being sexist after saying his wife "knows her place (in the kitchen)" he is completely bewildered by these comments and insisted that he takes good care of his wife.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/StealthPun" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/StealthPun">Stealth Pun</a>: Many of the Twitter Shout-Outs, such as "AlphaKennyOne", "IsleOfRussia", and "Phil_McCracken".</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/StockSoundEffect" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/StockSoundEffect">Stock Sound Effect</a>: A rare live example; whenever Ghost gets especially upset, expect to hear cans (most likely beer) being shoved off a table. It's often referred to as "cans.wav", alluding to the uncertainty over if it is real or not.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/StupidStatementDanceMix" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/StupidStatementDanceMix">Stupid Statement Dance Mix</a>:<ul><li> Unfortunately (well, to him), a lot of the one-liners he's said (like "melting pot of friendship", "HAMBOOOOONE", etc.) end up being perfect material for these. When people got the bright idea to start playing them right <em>at</em> him during calls, Ghost reacted accordingly. That is, he hates them to no end.</li><li> Four words, <a class="urllink" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LtqIxGzwSuw">"Melting Pot of Alcohol"<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a><ul><li> There are, as of now, quite a few remixes <em>of that remix,</em> among them <a class="urllink" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=uctCq1um3Ko">one that samples "Giggle at the Ghostie,"<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a> <a class="urllink" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=7L_-JG0ENls">an 8-bit remix,<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a> <a class="urllink" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vZo26RpSjYU&amp;feature=related">a mashup with "Party Rock Anthem,"<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a> and <a class="urllink" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=MswCIbjU0Mo">a stoner remix.<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a></li></ul></li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SuddenlyShouting" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SuddenlyShouting">Suddenly CANS</a>: Most instances of <em>cans.wav</em> start out with Ghost giving what sounds like just a mildly angry response only to be cut off by the sound of Mic Vs. Aluminium with him heard screaming at the offender over the cacophony.<ul><li> "I can't believe you <strong>SCUMBAGS!!!!</strong>"</li><li> Cranked up to 11 when he randomly shouted at a Helen Keller Deaf Mute on the October 6, 2016 show.<ul><li> "562, Radio Graffiti. .......<strong>562, WHY DON'T YOU SAY SOMETHING, YOU STUPID PIECE OF CRAP?!?</strong>"</li></ul></li><li> "The sun is warm...the grass is green....and-wait what the hell is that <em><strong>GOD DAMN PANDA-</strong></em> <em>*cans.wav*</em></li><li> On February 26th, 2018, Ghost tries to get a good drink out of the cooler.</li></ul><div class="indent"> <strong>Ghost</strong>: All I got is crappy cans? ALL I GOT IS CRAPPY CANS, ENGINEER!?</div><div class="indent"> *Engineer says something inaudible*</div><div class="indent"> <strong>Ghost</strong>: GOD DAMMIT! GOD DAMN- *cans.wav* I'VE GOT ENOUGH CRAPPY CANS, MAN!</div></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SurroundedByIdiots" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SurroundedByIdiots">Surrounded By Fruitbowls</a>: Ghost.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TantrumThrowing" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TantrumThrowing">Tantrum Throwing</a>: The cans.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TemptingFate" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TemptingFate">Tempting Fate</a>: Whenever he specifically asks the listeners NOT to remix him with something. Take a wild guess what call is waiting for him the next day.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ThatCameOutWrong" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ThatCameOutWrong">That Came Out Wrong</a>:<ul><li> <a class="urllink" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=8KUUADqj2GA">"If anyone came at me trying to be busy badass, you know I always walk around out here in Texas ... with my strap on.<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gi