/pmwiki.php/Main/Troll">Trolls</a>: They come. They try to make him look like a fool. They succeed. He fires back by claiming they're wholly responsible for America's bad economy. There has been much speculation regarding whether Ghost <em>himself</em> is a "cannibal troll" deliberately cultivating these trolls as a form of meta-trolling. Following the show's (original) cancellation on May 23, 2012, it was revealed in a final chat session that <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">this theory is both right and wrong at the same time. Some rages (specifically the meme-related ones) <em>were</em> exaggerated and he is, in fact, friends with the troll Amy Daly, but he also really is a Texan capitalist and was a genuinely angry man when he started the show- three hours a day of ranting about politics and being trolled helped him get it all out of his system.</span></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Troperiffic" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Troperiffic">Troperiffic</a>: This is an awfully-long page for a political radio show, no?</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TroublingUnchildlikeBehavior" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TroublingUnchildlikeBehavior">Troubling Unchildlike Behavior</a>: Regular caller Asho smoked weed and looks at pornography, knowing that his mom is elsewhere hitting on strangers.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheUnintelligible" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheUnintelligible">The Unintelligible</a>: Engineer and the Guru.</li></ul><ul><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/UnknownRival" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/UnknownRival">Unknown Rival</a>: "ALEX JONES IS RUINING AMERICA!!" <em>*cans.wav*</em></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/UnstoppableRage" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/UnstoppableRage">Unstoppable Rage</a>: Especially prevalent when his show was called True Conservative Radio. He'd start yelling for about a few minutes over anything. Whether it was bad parents, a <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Troll" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Troll">Troll</a> or over anything, he'd start yelling at the <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HairTriggerTemper" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HairTriggerTemper">slightest twitch</a>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/UnsympatheticComedyProtagonist" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/UnsympatheticComedyProtagonist">Unsympathetic Comedy Protagonist</a>: Ghost unwittingly made himself into this, and he's only become both more unsympathetic <em>and</em> more hilarious as the years go on.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/VanInBlack" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/VanInBlack">Van in Black</a>: Ghost's stated reason for going on a four year hiatus: Apparently, <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SmallNameBigEgo" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SmallNameBigEgo">he had made some powerful enemies within the government with his broadcasts</a> and they started sending "ice cream vans, parked outside his house, in the middle of winter" to monitor him and his family. <em>Right.</em> Definitely not because the trolls finally got to him. Not because of that.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/VerbalTic" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/VerbalTic">Verbal Tic</a> / <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/YouKeepUsingThatWord" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/YouKeepUsingThatWord">You Keep Using That Word</a>:<ul><li> "Trans-testicle" instead of transsexual (which spread out into the troll usage), "Canadia" (pronounced like "Canadian") instead of Canada, etc.</li><li> Ghost also throws around variants of "fruit" as an adjective, noun, and verb for something that is, or is becoming overly flamboyant or gay. Thus, the term "fruitbowl" is used as a describer for things that meet this criteria.</li><li> Whenever talking to or about Latinos (such as Goofy_Bone and Asho), Ghost will invariably mention "bean and cheese". "Hispandex" is also a common word in Ghost's vernacular.</li><li> In September 2011, advocated the use of the term "hambone" to refer to and subtly mock people who he views as "fat jelly-asses" who live off welfare and otherwise contribute nothing to society. However, it'd help if all the prank callers didn't go around calling <em>him</em> one.</li><li> The various trolls have their own verbal tics. Ghetto Capitalist has "baby", Tub Guy has "Oh my!" and Equestrian Citizen has the n-word.</li><li> And he calls xarahox a "penist".</li><li> When he's particularly angry, he'll add "fer Christ sake" to the end of just about every sentence.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/VerySpecialEpisode" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/VerySpecialEpisode">Very Special Episode</a>: March 27th, 2012, in which he devoted the entire show to the Trayvon Martin case. This lead to more serious callers than usual, some agreeing with him and some debating him. <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MoodWhiplash" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MoodWhiplash">Everybody else</a> played splices of <img src="/images/article-hreficon-ymmv.png" class="ymmv1 rounded" title="This example contains a YMMV entry. It should be moved to the YMMV tab."><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CrossesTheLineTwice" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CrossesTheLineTwice">Ghost urinating on his family.</a><ul><li> November 8th, 2016 was dedicated solely to Election Night coverage, with it being broadcast later in the day and only 1 failtroll being picked up with no reaction.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheVillainSucksSong" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheVillainSucksSong">"The Villain Sucks" Song</a>:<ul><li> "<a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PrecisionFStrike" title="/