f Homeland Security agents had threatened him and his wife and double dipped his nachos which forced him to cancel the show and loose his sleep for the day. Ghost was still extremely angry over the incident and frequently threatened to beat up one of the agents. This was all made worse after trolls picked up on the double dipping and called him <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Cuckold" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Cuckold">a Cuck</a> for letting the agents double dip his chips. This drove ghost into extreme rage, with his voice going rather deep screaming "I WANNA SEE HIS FACE!" and made him both <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RageQuit" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RageQuit">Rage Quit</a> and break the Cans World Record during the show.</li><li> September 13th, 2016. Ghost was calling numbers from a "Guccifer 2.0 leak" until Ghost caught the wind of a scheme where people in The Brony Network chat tried to trick Ghost into calling the FBI. He ended the show soon thereafter, making this the shortest non-announcement episode of TCR, ever.</li><li> September 23rd, 2016. TCR Civil War fires off after Ghost releases Engineer's autograph for sale. Ghost did an <em>unbeaten record of 36 cans.wav</em> during the show and shouted so loud that he broke his voice for several days.</li><li> October 3rd, 2016. A Graffiti call of various members of the Inner Circle (including Teutonic Plague) pledging allegiance to "Team Engin' Ear", and a clip of Donald Trump saying he approves this message sent Ghost into a <em>Canocalypse</em> (even though it was meant to be a harmless prank). This was followed by several minutes of crying and speechlessness at "THE BETRAYAL!!" Finally, Ghost <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RageQuit" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RageQuit">Rage Quit</a> and as of present, <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NothingIsTheSameAnymore" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NothingIsTheSameAnymore">the Inner Circle has been in hot water with him since.</a></li><li> October 7th, 2016. Ghost finds out that G is ripping off a caller from another show known as "The Toilet Guy". Things get worse after Ghost calls G during the show. G initially tries to deny the claims, but finally admits he's guilty after Ghost gets tweeted pictures from TheBronyNetwork's chatroom of him admitting he's Toilet Guy. Additionally he ends up admitting that not only was he ripping off Toilet Guy, but that he also likes anime, sending Ghost into an impressive storm of rage and causing him to <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RageQuit" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RageQuit">Rage Quit</a>. After the show G threatened that he was going to kill himself, forcing Ghost to hold an emergency Inner Circle meeting where it turns out G was lying about his suicide threat, leading to Ghost mouthing him off and banning him from the show for several months.</li><li> January 27th, 2017. Ghost comes to realize the <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AwfulTruth" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AwfulTruth">Awful Truth</a> that the Alt Right are Russian backed shills after looking into the background of Alt Right figurehead Richard B. Spencer and finding out that his wife is a Russian communist sympathizer. This revelation makes Ghost question many of his views and why he even feeds the trolls on his show. Toward the end Ghost threatened to leave the show for good, and ended the broadcast 90 minutes early.</li><li> February 2nd, 2017. During Radio Graffiti, a clip of people in the Inner Circle chatroom is played, with them going off about how Ghost thinks he's right about everything and people just blindly follow him. Ghost ends the show and immediately kicks the offending members in the chatroom, causing a rift in the community between Ghost and the trolls once again.</li><li> May 3rd, 2017. After going off on a rant about the Youth of America and certain Inner Circle members he's at odds with, Ghost begins contemplating ending the show again. During Radio Graffiti, someone calls in with audio from an argument between Ghost and Trumping Capitalist, causing a <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RageQuit" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RageQuit">Rage Quit</a> and Ghost to say that he's shutting down the Inner Circle, replacing it with the Inner Triangle.</li><li> May 8th, 2017. Ghost announces that the show will be put on an indefinite hiatus due to the cartoon fetishists in the community. This was followed up by several purges in the Inner Circle and many dramas.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WhamLine" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WhamLine">Wham Line</a>: On May 3, 2012's Radio Graffiti segment, a caller pretended to be on his side, talking about the government and people with EBTs...until he says, "As of this Tuesday, my EBT card has your avatar on it. So, every time I swipe, I know..." He got cut off mid-sentence, complete with Ghost raging.<ul><li> The call on February 2nd, 2017 revealing Elfoxoloco's true feelings about Ghost, calling him out for ignoring debates and opposing opinions, and calling out the groupthink mentality that surrounds him.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WhatHaveIBecome" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WhatHaveIBecome">What Have I Become?</a>: On Episode 13 of Ghost's Youtube broadcast "The Ghost Show" Ghost realizes the significant decrease in quality of his show, having it degrade from a semi-serious source of financial advice and political opinions to a three-hour-long spectacle of him drinking, crying, and shouting at trolls (Who have also taken to literally doing the show for him due to his inability to do so due to being so occupied by their antics.)<dl><dd><div class="indent">"Ghost: What have I become man, seriously? What the hell have I become? I mean I'm just.. I'm just some <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheChewToy" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheChewToy">punching bag</a> for <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheBully" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheBully">cyberbullies</a> man, that's what I am! That's what I am now! *sniffles* That's what I am..."</div></dd></dl></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WhyWeAreBummedCommunismFell" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WhyWeAreBummedCommunismFell">Why We're Bummed Capitalism Fell</a>: For a community who spent a year deliberately driving him insane, people were pretty upset when Ghost announced he was quitting the show, and rejoiced upon his return.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WorthyOpponent" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WorthyOpponent">Worthy Opponent</a>: Tzeki was this before he was <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PutOnABus" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PutOnABus">Put on a Bus</a> in early 2012.<dl><dd><div class="indent"><strong>Ghost:</strong> That was some pretty good lulz!</div></dd></dl><ul><li> Ghost's speech while giving Ghetto Capitalist the Troll of the Year Award had hints of this.</li><li> Ghost also considered Boat073 a talented splicer, and said he had a future in audio engineering.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WrongGenreSavvy" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WrongGenreSavvy">Wrong Genre Savvy</a>: Ghost used to be this around the time trolls first started bugging him. <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CharacterDevelopment" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CharacterDevelopment">Over time</a> he seems to have wised up a little bit. Doesn't prevent the trolls from making him lose it, though.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/YankTheDogsChain" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/YankTheDogsChain">Yank the Dog's Chain</a>: He returned with a short broadcast in November of 2015, giving his perspective on some of the events that had transpired in the three years since his absence, and left open the possibility of a return show on Christmas Eve or New Years Eve. While this briefly rejuvenated the TCR fandom, there were no broadcasts on either holiday and as of January 2016 no signs of a permanent return are apparent.<ul><li> Subverted with the <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HesBack" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HesBack">triumphant return of Ghost and True Capitalist Radio in March 2016.</a></li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/YinYangBomb" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/YinYangBomb">Yin-Yang Bomb</a>: An easy way to piss Ghost off with a Twitter Shout-Out name is to simply combine something he likes or endorses with something he <em>hates</em>; "Herman_CainDusky", "True_Fapitalist", "Templeton_Sanders", "The_Trans_Trump", ect.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/YouAreWhatYouHate" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/YouAreWhatYouHate">You Are What You Hate</a>: Gee, Ghost really seems to hate people who are <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Hypocrite" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Hypocrite">fat, lazy, racist, sexist, redneck, insensitive conspiracy theorists who make America look bad, doesn't he?</a> Especially Alex Jones, who is not only all of the above - and more - but even <em>sounds</em> uncannily similar to Ghost. <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BerserkButton" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BerserkButton">Just don't tell him that.</a></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/YouDoNOTWantToKnow" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/YouDoNOTWantToKnow">You Do NOT Want To Know</a>: Gasgara's relationship with Suspicious Tumbleweed was this. As the True Capitalist Radio Wiki put it:<div class="indent">Gasgara's only friend was a strange Canadian teenager who goes by the username Suspicious Tumbleweed. She seemed to have a certain appreciation of Gasgara's "personality". They often conversed over Twitter discussing Skype and Xbox LIVE interactions. This relationship disturbed and confused each and every True Capitalist Radio listener in the first run of said show.</div></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/YourApprovalFillsMeWithShame" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/YourApprovalFillsMeWithShame">Your Approval Fills Me with Shame</a>: Tri$ha, Tub Guy, and Ghetto Capitalist (natch) all approve strongly of Ghost's capitalistic views... but since they're (respectively) a transgender woman, a flamboyant omnisexual, and a welfare abuser, Ghost is absolutely enraged at this hijacking of his philosophy.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/YourMom" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/YourMom">Your Mom</a>: Sometimes used as a retort.</li></ul></div><p></p><hr><p><em>GYAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHRHHHHHHHGH! GET HIM OFF, ENGINEEEEEEEEEEEER! GET THAT STUPID FRUITY-ASS FRUITBOWL OFF!</em></p><p><em>THAT'S IT! I AM DONE! I AM DONE! STICK A FORK IN ME I'M DONE! I'M GONE! I'M GOING TO 6TH STREET! IT'S MILLA' TIME, BABY! GET ME OUT OF HERE, ENGINEER!</em></p><p><em>You've been listening to True Capitalist Radio. The thoughts, views, ideas, comments, and opinions of the host of the show are...absolutely his.</em></p><hr>
</div>
